{"cells":[{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"Wf5KrEb6vrkR"},"source":["# Welcome to Colab!"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"1edGr7JPAZyr"},"source":["## Google Colab is available in VS Code!\n","![logo.webp](data:image/webp;base64,)\n","\n","Try the new [Google Colab extension](https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=Google.colab) for Visual Studio Code. You can get up and running in just a few clicks:\n","\n","*  In VS Code, open the ***Extensions*** view and search for 'Google Colab' to install.\n","*  Open the kernel selector by creating or opening any `.ipynb` notebook file in your local workspace and either running a cell or clicking the ***Select Kernel*** button in the top right.\n","*  Click ***Colab*** and then select your desired runtime, sign in with your Google account, and you're all set!\n","\n","See more details in our [announcement blog here](https://developers.googleblog.com/google-colab-is-coming-to-vs-code)."]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"C1XfGyQXQK1n"},"source":["## Access popular AI models via Google-Colab-AI Without an API Key\n","All users have access to most popular LLMs via the `google-colab-ai` Python library, and paid users have access to a wider selection of models. For more details, refer to the [getting started with google colab ai](https://colab.research.google.com/github/googlecolab/colabtools/blob/main/notebooks/Getting_started_with_google_colab_ai.ipynb).\n","\n"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":6,"metadata":{"id":"JQesyTg7QSU-","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1780641073883,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":1094,"user":{"displayName":"","userId":""}}},"outputs":[],"source":["from google.colab import ai\n","response = ai.generate_text(\"What is the capital of France?\")"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"-sdyeRMXPvU_"},"source":["## Explore the Gemini API\n","The Gemini API gives you access to Gemini models created by Google DeepMind. Gemini models are built from the ground up to be multimodal, so you can reason seamlessly across text, images, code, and audio.\n","\n","**How to get started?**\n","*  Go to [Google AI Studio](https://aistudio.google.com/) and log in with your Google account.\n","*  [Create an API key](https://aistudio.google.com/app/apikey).\n","* Use a quickstart for [Python](https://colab.research.google.com/github/google-gemini/cookbook/blob/main/quickstarts/Get_started.ipynb), or call the REST API using [curl](https://colab.research.google.com/github/google-gemini/cookbook/blob/main/quickstarts/rest/Prompting_REST.ipynb).\n","\n","**Discover Gemini's advanced capabilities**\n","*  Play with Gemini [multimodal outputs](https://colab.research.google.com/github/google-gemini/cookbook/blob/main/quickstarts/Image-out.ipynb), mixing text and images in an iterative way.\n","*  Discover the [multimodal Live API](https://colab.research.google.com/github/google-gemini/cookbook/blob/main/quickstarts/Get_started_LiveAPI.ipynb ) (demo [here](https://aistudio.google.com/live)).\n","*  Learn how to [analyze images and detect items in your pictures](https://colab.research.google.com/github/google-gemini/cookbook/blob/main/quickstarts/Spatial_understanding.ipynb\") using Gemini (bonus, there's a [3D version](https://colab.research.google.com/github/google-gemini/cookbook/blob/main/examples/Spatial_understanding_3d.ipynb) as well!).\n","*  Unlock the power of [Gemini thinking model](https://colab.research.google.com/github/google-gemini/cookbook/blob/main/quickstarts/Get_started_thinking.ipynb), capable of solving complex task with its inner thoughts.\n","      \n","**Explore complex use cases**\n","*  Use [Gemini grounding capabilities](https://colab.research.google.com/github/google-gemini/cookbook/blob/main/examples/Search_grounding_for_research_report.ipynb) to create a report on a company based on what the model can find on internet.\n","*  Extract [invoices and form data from PDF](https://colab.research.google.com/github/google-gemini/cookbook/blob/main/examples/Pdf_structured_outputs_on_invoices_and_forms.ipynb) in a structured way.\n","*  Create [illustrations based on a whole book](https://colab.research.google.com/github/google-gemini/cookbook/blob/main/examples/Book_illustration.ipynb) using Gemini large context window and Imagen.\n","\n","To learn more, check out the [Gemini cookbook](https://github.com/google-gemini/cookbook) or visit the [Gemini API documentation](https://ai.google.dev/docs/).\n"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"Nma_JWh-W-IF"},"source":["Colab now has AI features powered by [Gemini](https://gemini.google.com). The video below provides information on how to use these features, whether you're new to Python, or a seasoned veteran.\n","\n","<center>\n","  <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=V7RXyqFUR98\" target=\"_blank\">\n","  <img alt='Thumbnail for a video showing 3 AI-powered Google Colab features' src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" height=\"188\" width=\"336\">\n","  </a>\n","</center>"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"5fCEDCU_qrC0"},"source":["<div class=\"markdown-google-sans\">\n","  <h2>What is Colab?</h2>\n","</div>\n","\n","Colab, or \"Colaboratory\", allows you to write and execute Python in your browser, with\n","- Zero configuration required\n","- Access to GPUs free of charge\n","- Easy sharing\n","\n","Whether you're a **student**, a **data scientist** or an **AI researcher**, Colab can make your work easier. Watch [Introduction to Colab](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=inN8seMm7UI) or [Colab Features You May Have Missed](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=rNgswRZ2C1Y) to learn more, or just get started below!"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"GJBs_flRovLc"},"source":["<div class=\"markdown-google-sans\">\n","\n","## **Getting started**\n","</div>\n","\n","The document you are reading is not a static web page, but an interactive environment called a **Colab notebook** that lets you write and execute code.\n","\n","For example, here is a **code cell** with a short Python script that computes a value, stores it in a variable, and prints the result:"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":7,"metadata":{"id":"gJr_9dXGpJ05","outputId":"49e68dc1-cfae-4636-e50e-423b977c7ff6","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1780641073893,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":5,"user":{"displayName":"","userId":""}},"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"}},"outputs":[{"output_type":"execute_result","data":{"text/plain":["86400"]},"metadata":{},"execution_count":7}],"source":["seconds_in_a_day = 24 * 60 * 60\n","seconds_in_a_day"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"2fhs6GZ4qFMx"},"source":["To execute the code in the above cell, select it with a click and then either press the play button to the left of the code, or use the keyboard shortcut \"Command/Ctrl+Enter\". To edit the code, just click the cell and start editing.\n","\n","Variables that you define in one cell can later be used in other cells:"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":8,"metadata":{"id":"-gE-Ez1qtyIA","outputId":"c253b72a-c4e2-4f47-c0f1-c2db06502df5","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1780641073918,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":18,"user":{"displayName":"","userId":""}},"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"}},"outputs":[{"output_type":"execute_result","data":{"text/plain":["604800"]},"metadata":{},"execution_count":8}],"source":["seconds_in_a_week = 7 * seconds_in_a_day\n","seconds_in_a_week"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"lSrWNr3MuFUS"},"source":["Colab notebooks allow you to combine **executable code** and **rich text** in a single document, along with **images**, **HTML**, **LaTeX** and more. When you create your own Colab notebooks, they are stored in your Google Drive account. You can easily share your Colab notebooks with co-workers or friends, allowing them to comment on your notebooks or even edit them. To learn more, see [Overview of Colab](/notebooks/basic_features_overview.ipynb). To create a new Colab notebook you can use the File menu above, or use the following link: [create a new Colab notebook](http://colab.research.google.com#create=true).\n","\n","Colab notebooks are Jupyter notebooks that are hosted by Colab. To learn more about the Jupyter project, see [jupyter.org](https://www.jupyter.org)."]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"UdRyKR44dcNI"},"source":["<div class=\"markdown-google-sans\">\n","\n","## Data science\n","</div>\n","\n","With Colab you can harness the full power of popular Python libraries to analyze and visualize data. The code cell below uses **numpy** to generate some random data, and uses **matplotlib** to visualize it. To edit the code, just click the cell and start editing."]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"4_kCnsPUqS6o"},"source":["You can import your own data into Colab notebooks from your Google Drive account, including from spreadsheets, as well as from Github and many other sources. To learn more about importing data, and how Colab can be used for data science, see the links below under [Working with Data](#working-with-data)."]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":9,"metadata":{"colab":{"height":334,"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"C4HZx7Gndbrh","outputId":"7007eac6-78de-4cdb-927e-3d0aacfc9ba2","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1780641074185,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":252,"user":{"displayName":"","userId":""}}},"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<IPython.core.display.Markdown object>"],"text/markdown":"![Sample Visualization](data:image/png;base64,)"},"metadata":{}}],"source":["import numpy as np\n","import IPython.display as display\n","from matplotlib import pyplot as plt\n","import io\n","import base64\n","\n","ys = 200 + np.random.randn(100)\n","x = [x for x in range(len(ys))]\n","\n","fig = plt.figure(figsize=(4, 3), facecolor='w')\n","plt.plot(x, ys, '-')\n","plt.fill_between(x, ys, 195, where=(ys > 195), facecolor='g', alpha=0.6)\n","plt.title(\"Sample Visualization\", fontsize=10)\n","\n","data = io.BytesIO()\n","plt.savefig(data)\n","image = F\"data:image/png;base64,{base64.b64encode(data.getvalue()).decode()}\"\n","alt = \"Sample Visualization\"\n","display.display(display.Markdown(F\"\"\"![{alt}]({image})\"\"\"))\n","plt.close(fig)"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"VYV91hbKwP2J"},"source":["Colab notebooks execute code on Google's cloud servers, meaning you can leverage the power of Google hardware, including [GPUs and TPUs](#using-accelerated-hardware), regardless of the power of your machine. All you need is a browser.\n","\n","For example, if you find yourself waiting for **pandas** code to finish running and want to go faster, you can switch to a GPU Runtime and use libraries like [RAPIDS cuDF](https://rapids.ai/cudf-pandas) that provide zero-code-change acceleration."]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"vwnNlNIEwoZ8"},"source":["To learn more about accelerating pandas on Colab, see the [10 minute guide](https://colab.research.google.com/github/rapidsai-community/showcase/blob/main/getting_started_tutorials/cudf_pandas_colab_demo.ipynb) or\n"," [US stock market data analysis demo](https://colab.research.google.com/github/rapidsai-community/showcase/blob/main/getting_started_tutorials/cudf_pandas_stocks_demo.ipynb)."]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"OwuxHmxllTwN"},"source":["<div class=\"markdown-google-sans\">\n","\n","## Machine learning\n","</div>\n","\n","With Colab you can import an image dataset, train an image classifier on it, and evaluate the model, all in just [a few lines of code](https://colab.research.google.com/github/tensorflow/docs/blob/master/site/en/tutorials/quickstart/beginner.ipynb)."]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"ufxBm1yRnruN"},"source":["Colab is used extensively in the machine learning community with applications including:\n","- Getting started with TensorFlow\n","- Developing and training neural networks\n","- Experimenting with TPUs\n","- Disseminating AI research\n","- Creating tutorials\n","\n","To see sample Colab notebooks that demonstrate machine learning applications, see the [machine learning examples](#machine-learning-examples) below."]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"-Rh3-Vt9Nev9"},"source":["<div class=\"markdown-google-sans\">\n","\n","## More Resources\n","\n","### Working with Notebooks in Colab\n","\n","</div>\n","\n","- [Overview of Colab](/notebooks/basic_features_overview.ipynb)\n","- [Guide to Markdown](/notebooks/markdown_guide.ipynb)\n","- [Importing libraries and installing dependencies](/notebooks/snippets/importing_libraries.ipynb)\n","- [Saving and loading notebooks in GitHub](https://colab.research.google.com/github/googlecolab/colabtools/blob/main/notebooks/colab-github-demo.ipynb)\n","- [Interactive forms](/notebooks/forms.ipynb)\n","- [Interactive widgets](/notebooks/widgets.ipynb)\n","\n","<div class=\"markdown-google-sans\">\n","\n","<a name=\"working-with-data\"></a>\n","### Working with Data\n","</div>\n","\n","- [Loading data: Drive, Sheets, and Google Cloud Storage](/notebooks/io.ipynb)\n","- [Charts: visualizing data](/notebooks/charts.ipynb)\n","- [Getting started with BigQuery](/notebooks/bigquery.ipynb)\n","\n","<div class=\"markdown-google-sans\">\n","\n","### Machine Learning\n","\n","<div>\n","\n","These are a few of the notebooks related to Machine Learning, including Google's online Machine Learning course. See the [full course website](https://developers.google.com/machine-learning/crash-course/) for more.\n","- [Intro to Pandas DataFrame](https://colab.research.google.com/github/google/eng-edu/blob/main/ml/cc/exercises/pandas_dataframe_ultraquick_tutorial.ipynb)\n","- [Intro to RAPIDS cuDF to accelerate pandas](https://nvda.ws/rapids-cudf)\n","- [Getting Started with cuML's accelerator mode](https://colab.research.google.com/github/rapidsai-community/showcase/blob/main/getting_started_tutorials/cuml_sklearn_colab_demo.ipynb)\n","\n","<div class=\"markdown-google-sans\">\n","\n","<a name=\"using-accelerated-hardware\"></a>\n","### Using Accelerated Hardware\n","</div>\n","\n","- [Train a CNN to classify handwritten digits on the MNIST dataset using Flax NNX API](https://colab.research.google.com/github/google/flax/blob/main/docs_nnx/mnist_tutorial.ipynb)\n","- [Train a Vision Transformer (ViT) for image classification with JAX](https://colab.research.google.com/github/jax-ml/jax-ai-stack/blob/main/docs/source/JAX_Vision_transformer.ipynb)\n","- [Text classification with a transformer language model using JAX](https://colab.research.google.com/github/jax-ml/jax-ai-stack/blob/main/docs/source/JAX_transformer_text_classification.ipynb)"]},{"cell_type":"code","source":[],"metadata":{"id":"y9wK8rZcdKUY","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1780641074189,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":2,"user":{"displayName":"","userId":""}}},"execution_count":9,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"P-H6Lw1vyNNd"},"source":["<div class=\"markdown-google-sans\">\n","\n","<a name=\"machine-learning-examples\"></a>\n","\n","### Featured examples\n","\n","</div>\n","\n","- [Train a miniGPT language model with JAX AI Stack](https://docs.jaxstack.ai/en/latest/JAX_for_LLM_pretraining.html)\n","- [LoRA/QLoRA finetuning for LLM using Tunix](https://github.com/google/tunix/blob/main/examples/qlora_gemma.ipynb)\n","- [Parameter-efficient fine-tuning of Gemma with LoRA and QLoRA](https://keras.io/examples/keras_recipes/parameter_efficient_finetuning_of_gemma_with_lora_and_qlora/)\n","- [Loading Hugging Face Transformers Checkpoints](https://keras.io/keras_hub/guides/hugging_face_keras_integration/)\n","- [8-bit Integer Quantization in Keras](https://keras.io/guides/int8_quantization_in_keras/)\n","- [Float8 training and inference with a simple Transformer model](https://keras.io/examples/keras_recipes/float8_training_and_inference_with_transformer/)\n","- [Pretraining a Transformer from scratch with KerasHub](https://keras.io/keras_hub/guides/transformer_pretraining/)\n","- [Simple MNIST convnet](https://keras.io/examples/vision/mnist_convnet/)\n","- [Image classification from scratch using Keras 3](https://keras.io/examples/vision/image_classification_from_scratch/)\n","- [Image Classification with KerasHub](https://keras.io/keras_hub/guides/classification_with_keras_hub/)\n"]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["import yfinance as yf\n","import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n","import matplotlib.patches as mpatches\n","\n","# --- Step 1: Download real OHLC data ---\n","# Using Reliance Industries (NSE) — relevant for Indian market\n","ticker = yf.Ticker(\"RELIANCE.NS\")\n","df = ticker.history(period=\"3mo\", interval=\"1d\")\n","\n","print(\"Raw OHLC Data (first 5 rows):\")\n","print(df[['Open', 'High', 'Low', 'Close', 'Volume']].head())\n","\n","# --- Step 2: Calculate candlestick components manually ---\n","df['body']        = abs(df['Close'] - df['Open'])\n","df['upper_wick']  = df['High'] - df[['Open', 'Close']].max(axis=1)\n","df['lower_wick']  = df[['Open', 'Close']].min(axis=1) - df['Low']\n","df['is_bullish']  = df['Close'] > df['Open']\n","\n","print(\"\\nCandlestick Components (first 5 rows):\")\n","print(df[['Open','High','Low','Close','body','upper_wick','lower_wick','is_bullish']].head())\n","\n","# --- Step 3: Draw a simple candlestick chart manually ---\n","fig, (ax1, ax2) = plt.subplots(2, 1, figsize=(14, 8),\n","                                gridspec_kw={'height_ratios': [3, 1]})\n","\n","recent = df.tail(30)  # last 30 days\n","\n","for i, (date, row) in enumerate(recent.iterrows()):\n","    color = 'green' if row['is_bullish'] else 'red'\n","\n","    # Draw the wick (thin vertical line from Low to High)\n","    ax1.plot([i, i], [row['Low'], row['High']], color=color, linewidth=1)\n","\n","    # Draw the body (thick rectangle from Open to Close)\n","    bottom = min(row['Open'], row['Close'])\n","    ax1.bar(i, row['body'], bottom=bottom, color=color,\n","            width=0.6, alpha=0.8)\n","\n","ax1.set_title('Reliance Industries — 30-Day Candlestick Chart', fontsize=13)\n","ax1.set_ylabel('Price (₹)')\n","ax1.set_xticks(range(0, len(recent), 5))\n","ax1.set_xticklabels([str(d.date()) for d in recent.index[::5]], rotation=45)\n","\n","# Volume bars\n","colors = ['green' if b else 'red' for b in recent['is_bullish']]\n","ax2.bar(range(len(recent)), recent['Volume'] / 1e6, color=colors, alpha=0.7)\n","ax2.set_ylabel('Volume (millions)')\n","ax2.set_xticks(range(0, len(recent), 5))\n","ax2.set_xticklabels([str(d.date()) for d in recent.index[::5]], rotation=45)\n","\n","plt.tight_layout()\n","plt.savefig('stage1_candlestick.png', dpi=150)\n","plt.show()\n","print(\"\\nChart saved as stage1_candlestick.png\")"],"metadata":{"id":"kDQR36KAdQXj","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1780641075491,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":1300,"user":{"displayName":"","userId":""}},"outputId":"b7d18dd3-6308-414e-8c8b-22dfd93a5eac","colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":1000}},"execution_count":10,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Raw OHLC Data (first 5 rows):\n","                                  Open         High          Low        Close  \\\n","Date                                                                            \n","2026-03-05 00:00:00+05:30  1346.872629  1392.561409  1346.872629  1383.005615   \n","2026-03-06 00:00:00+05:30  1390.072867  1417.744972  1383.901450  1398.334717   \n","2026-03-09 00:00:00+05:30  1368.671803  1422.821461  1363.694815  1417.446289   \n","2026-03-10 00:00:00+05:30  1424.015880  1424.911763  1394.153950  1402.316284   \n","2026-03-11 00:00:00+05:30  1418.342129  1427.400223  1377.232158  1383.801758   \n","\n","                             Volume  \n","Date                                 \n","2026-03-05 00:00:00+05:30  25957532  \n","2026-03-06 00:00:00+05:30  19311971  \n","2026-03-09 00:00:00+05:30  24870822  \n","2026-03-10 00:00:00+05:30  18071259  \n","2026-03-11 00:00:00+05:30  21848087  \n","\n","Candlestick Components (first 5 rows):\n","                                  Open         High          Low        Close  \\\n","Date                                                                            \n","2026-03-05 00:00:00+05:30  1346.872629  1392.561409  1346.872629  1383.005615   \n","2026-03-06 00:00:00+05:30  1390.072867  1417.744972  1383.901450  1398.334717   \n","2026-03-09 00:00:00+05:30  1368.671803  1422.821461  1363.694815  1417.446289   \n","2026-03-10 00:00:00+05:30  1424.015880  1424.911763  1394.153950  1402.316284   \n","2026-03-11 00:00:00+05:30  1418.342129  1427.400223  1377.232158  1383.801758   \n","\n","                                body  upper_wick  lower_wick  is_bullish  \n","Date                                                                      \n","2026-03-05 00:00:00+05:30  36.132986    9.555794    0.000000        True  \n","2026-03-06 00:00:00+05:30   8.261849   19.410255    6.171417        True  \n","2026-03-09 00:00:00+05:30  48.774486    5.375172    4.976988        True  \n","2026-03-10 00:00:00+05:30  21.699596    0.895882    8.162334       False  \n","2026-03-11 00:00:00+05:30  34.540371    9.058094    6.569600       False  \n"]},{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<Figure size 1400x800 with 2 Axes>"],"image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}},{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["\n","Chart saved as stage1_candlestick.png\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["import yfinance as yf\n","import pandas as pd\n","import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n","\n","# --- Step 1: Download data ---\n","ticker = yf.Ticker(\"RELIANCE.NS\")\n","df = ticker.history(period=\"6mo\", interval=\"1d\")\n","df = df[['Open', 'High', 'Low', 'Close', 'Volume']].copy()\n","\n","# --- Step 2: Calculate R_wb for every candle ---\n","def calculate_rwb(row):\n","    upper_wick = row['High'] - max(row['Open'], row['Close'])\n","    lower_wick = min(row['Open'], row['Close']) - row['Low']\n","    total_wick = upper_wick + lower_wick\n","    body       = abs(row['Open'] - row['Close'])\n","\n","    if body == 0:\n","        return None  # Doji candle — handle separately\n","\n","    return round(total_wick / body, 2)\n","\n","df['upper_wick'] = df['High'] - df[['Open','Close']].max(axis=1)\n","df['lower_wick'] = df[['Open','Close']].min(axis=1) - df['Low']\n","df['body']       = abs(df['Open'] - df['Close'])\n","df['R_wb']       = df.apply(calculate_rwb, axis=1)\n","\n","# --- Step 3: Flag high-rejection candles ---\n","REJECTION_THRESHOLD = 2.0  # R_wb > 2.0 = significant rejection\n","\n","df['is_rejection'] = df['R_wb'] > REJECTION_THRESHOLD\n","df['is_doji']      = df['body'] == 0\n","\n","print(\"=== Candle Analysis ===\")\n","print(f\"Total candles analyzed : {len(df)}\")\n","print(f\"Rejection candles (R_wb > {REJECTION_THRESHOLD}): {df['is_rejection'].sum()}\")\n","print(f\"Doji candles           : {df['is_doji'].sum()}\")\n","print()\n","print(\"=== Top 5 Highest Rejection Candles ===\")\n","top_rejections = df[['Open','High','Low','Close',\n","                      'body','upper_wick','lower_wick',\n","                      'R_wb']].nlargest(5, 'R_wb')\n","print(top_rejections.to_string())\n","\n","# --- Step 4: Visualize R_wb over time ---\n","fig, (ax1, ax2) = plt.subplots(2, 1, figsize=(14, 8),\n","                                gridspec_kw={'height_ratios': [2, 1]})\n","\n","# Price chart\n","ax1.plot(df.index, df['Close'], color='steelblue',\n","         linewidth=1.2, label='Close Price')\n","\n","# Mark rejection candles on price chart\n","rejections = df[df['is_rejection']]\n","ax1.scatter(rejections.index, rejections['Close'],\n","            color='red', zorder=5, s=40,\n","            label=f'Rejection (R_wb > {REJECTION_THRESHOLD})')\n","\n","ax1.set_title('Reliance Industries — Price with R_wb Rejection Flags', fontsize=13)\n","ax1.set_ylabel('Price (₹)')\n","ax1.legend()\n","\n","# R_wb chart\n","ax2.bar(df.index, df['R_wb'], color=[\n","    'red' if r else 'steelblue'\n","    for r in df['is_rejection']\n","], alpha=0.7, width=1)\n","\n","ax2.axhline(y=REJECTION_THRESHOLD, color='orange',\n","            linestyle='--', linewidth=1.5,\n","            label=f'Threshold = {REJECTION_THRESHOLD}')\n","\n","ax2.set_ylabel('R_wb Ratio')\n","ax2.set_title('R_wb Values Over Time (red bars = rejection signals)')\n","ax2.legend()\n","\n","plt.tight_layout()\n","plt.savefig('stage2_rwb.png', dpi=150)\n","plt.show()\n","print(\"\\nChart saved as stage2_rwb.png\")"],"metadata":{"id":"jxojIsF-eS88","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1780641076935,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":1443,"user":{"displayName":"","userId":""}},"outputId":"430f967c-e11c-4a61-d8b7-121729f275e4","colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":862}},"execution_count":11,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["=== Candle Analysis ===\n","Total candles analyzed : 124\n","Rejection candles (R_wb > 2.0): 41\n","Doji candles           : 3\n","\n","=== Top 5 Highest Rejection Candles ===\n","                                  Open         High          Low        Close      body  upper_wick  lower_wick    R_wb\n","Date                                                                                                                   \n","2026-04-20 00:00:00+05:30  1356.926120  1366.681066  1346.574081  1357.025757  0.099637    9.655309   10.352039  200.80\n","2026-05-25 00:00:00+05:30  1360.509587  1364.789724  1350.754641  1360.708618  0.199031    4.081106    9.754946   69.52\n","2026-01-27 00:00:00+05:30  1373.648786  1385.195374  1361.704013  1374.146484  0.497699   11.048890   11.944772   46.20\n","2026-01-16 00:00:00+05:30  1452.086190  1473.188572  1448.403145  1451.190308  0.895882   21.102382    2.787162   26.67\n","2026-04-08 00:00:00+05:30  1342.791475  1344.384087  1320.096359  1341.597046  1.194429    1.592612   21.500687   19.33\n"]},{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<Figure size 1400x800 with 2 Axes>"],"image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}},{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["\n","Chart saved as stage2_rwb.png\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["import yfinance as yf\n","import pandas as pd\n","import numpy as np\n","import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n","import matplotlib.patches as patches\n","\n","# --- Step 1: Download data ---\n","ticker = yf.Ticker(\"RELIANCE.NS\")\n","df = ticker.history(period=\"1y\", interval=\"1d\")\n","df = df[['Open','High','Low','Close','Volume']].copy()\n","df.reset_index(inplace=True)\n","\n","print(f\"Loaded {len(df)} trading days of data\")\n","\n","# --- Step 2: Find swing highs and swing lows ---\n","# A swing high = a candle whose High is higher than N candles\n","# on both sides. These are natural resistance candidates.\n","# A swing low  = a candle whose Low is lower than N candles\n","# on both sides. These are natural support candidates.\n","\n","def find_swing_highs(df, lookback=5):\n","    \"\"\"\n","    A swing high at index i means:\n","    df['High'][i] is the highest value in the window\n","    [i-lookback : i+lookback]\n","    \"\"\"\n","    swing_highs = []\n","    for i in range(lookback, len(df) - lookback):\n","        window = df['High'][i-lookback : i+lookback+1]\n","        if df['High'][i] == window.max():\n","            swing_highs.append(i)\n","    return swing_highs\n","\n","def find_swing_lows(df, lookback=5):\n","    \"\"\"\n","    A swing low at index i means:\n","    df['Low'][i] is the lowest value in the window\n","    [i-lookback : i+lookback]\n","    \"\"\"\n","    swing_lows = []\n","    for i in range(lookback, len(df) - lookback):\n","        window = df['Low'][i-lookback : i+lookback+1]\n","        if df['Low'][i] == window.min():\n","            swing_lows.append(i)\n","    return swing_lows\n","\n","swing_high_indices = find_swing_highs(df, lookback=5)\n","swing_low_indices  = find_swing_lows(df,  lookback=5)\n","\n","print(f\"Swing highs found: {len(swing_high_indices)}\")\n","print(f\"Swing lows found : {len(swing_low_indices)}\")\n","\n","# --- Step 3: Cluster nearby swing points into zones ---\n","# If multiple swing highs are within 'tolerance' of each other,\n","# they form a single resistance zone.\n","\n","def cluster_levels(indices, prices, tolerance_pct=0.015):\n","    \"\"\"\n","    Groups swing points that are within tolerance_pct of each other\n","    into zones. Returns list of (zone_low, zone_high, strength).\n","    Strength = number of touches.\n","    \"\"\"\n","    levels = [prices[i] for i in indices]\n","    levels.sort()\n","\n","    zones = []\n","    used  = [False] * len(levels)\n","\n","    for i in range(len(levels)):\n","        if used[i]:\n","            continue\n","        cluster = [levels[i]]\n","        used[i] = True\n","        for j in range(i+1, len(levels)):\n","            if not used[j]:\n","                # Check if within tolerance of cluster mean\n","                cluster_mean = np.mean(cluster)\n","                if abs(levels[j] - cluster_mean) / cluster_mean < tolerance_pct:\n","                    cluster.append(levels[j])\n","                    used[j] = True\n","        zone_low    = min(cluster)\n","        zone_high   = max(cluster)\n","        strength    = len(cluster)  # number of touches\n","        zones.append((zone_low, zone_high, strength))\n","\n","    return zones\n","\n","resistance_zones = cluster_levels(\n","    swing_high_indices, df['High'].values, tolerance_pct=0.015\n",")\n","support_zones = cluster_levels(\n","    swing_low_indices, df['Low'].values, tolerance_pct=0.015\n",")\n","\n","# Keep only zones with 2+ touches (weak zones ignored)\n","resistance_zones = [(z, s) for z, s in\n","    [(z, z[2]) for z in resistance_zones] if s >= 2]\n","support_zones    = [(z, s) for z, s in\n","    [(z, z[2]) for z in support_zones]    if s >= 2]\n","\n","print(f\"\\nStrong resistance zones (2+ touches): {len(resistance_zones)}\")\n","print(f\"Strong support zones    (2+ touches): {len(support_zones)}\")\n","\n","# --- Step 4: Check if current price is near a zone ---\n","current_price = df['Close'].iloc[-1]\n","zone_proximity_pct = 0.02  # within 2% = \"at the zone\"\n","\n","print(f\"\\nCurrent price: ₹{current_price:.2f}\")\n","print(\"\\n=== Active Support Zones ===\")\n","for (low, high, strength), _ in support_zones[-5:]:\n","    mid = (low + high) / 2\n","    distance_pct = abs(current_price - mid) / current_price * 100\n","    at_zone = distance_pct < zone_proximity_pct * 100\n","    flag = \" <<< PRICE AT ZONE\" if at_zone else \"\"\n","    print(f\"  ₹{low:.2f} – ₹{high:.2f}  | Touches: {strength} | \"\n","          f\"Distance: {distance_pct:.1f}%{flag}\")\n","\n","print(\"\\n=== Active Resistance Zones ===\")\n","for (low, high, strength), _ in resistance_zones[-5:]:\n","    mid = (low + high) / 2\n","    distance_pct = abs(current_price - mid) / current_price * 100\n","    at_zone = distance_pct < zone_proximity_pct * 100\n","    flag = \" <<< PRICE AT ZONE\" if at_zone else \"\"\n","    print(f\"  ₹{low:.2f} – ₹{high:.2f}  | Touches: {strength} | \"\n","          f\"Distance: {distance_pct:.1f}%{flag}\")\n","\n","# --- Step 5: Visualize ---\n","fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(16, 8))\n","\n","# Plot closing price\n","ax.plot(df.index, df['Close'],\n","        color='steelblue', linewidth=1.2,\n","        label='Close Price', zorder=3)\n","\n","# Draw support zones (green shading)\n","for (low, high, strength), _ in support_zones:\n","    ax.axhspan(low, high, alpha=min(0.1 * strength, 0.4),\n","               color='green', zorder=1)\n","    ax.axhline(y=(low+high)/2, color='green',\n","               linestyle='--', linewidth=0.8, alpha=0.6)\n","\n","# Draw resistance zones (red shading)\n","for (low, high, strength), _ in resistance_zones:\n","    ax.axhspan(low, high, alpha=min(0.1 * strength, 0.4),\n","               color='red', zorder=1)\n","    ax.axhline(y=(low+high)/2, color='red',\n","               linestyle='--', linewidth=0.8, alpha=0.6)\n","\n","# Mark swing highs and lows\n","ax.scatter([df.index[i] for i in swing_high_indices],\n","           [df['High'][i] for i in swing_high_indices],\n","           color='red', marker='v', s=30, zorder=5,\n","           label='Swing High')\n","ax.scatter([df.index[i] for i in swing_low_indices],\n","           [df['Low'][i] for i in swing_low_indices],\n","           color='green', marker='^', s=30, zorder=5,\n","           label='Swing Low')\n","\n","# Current price line\n","ax.axhline(y=current_price, color='orange',\n","           linestyle='-', linewidth=1.5,\n","           label=f'Current: ₹{current_price:.2f}')\n","\n","ax.set_title('Reliance Industries — Support & Resistance Zone Map', fontsize=13)\n","ax.set_ylabel('Price (₹)')\n","ax.legend(loc='upper left')\n","plt.tight_layout()\n","plt.savefig('stage3_support_resistance.png', dpi=150)\n","plt.show()\n","print(\"\\nChart saved as stage3_support_resistance.png\")"],"metadata":{"id":"NlUbcqjoeuXu","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1780641127516,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":1000,"user":{"displayName":"","userId":""}},"outputId":"f5266714-245b-4b90-d8f3-8d183234748e","colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":1000}},"execution_count":12,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Loaded 250 trading days of data\n","Swing highs found: 15\n","Swing lows found : 12\n","\n","Strong resistance zones (2+ touches): 4\n","Strong support zones    (2+ touches): 2\n","\n","Current price: ₹1295.20\n","\n","=== Active Support Zones ===\n","  ₹1284.06 – ₹1306.56  | Touches: 4 | Distance: 0.0% <<< PRICE AT ZONE\n","  ₹1329.35 – ₹1357.22  | Touches: 5 | Distance: 3.7%\n","\n","=== Active Resistance Zones ===\n","  ₹1364.79 – ₹1366.68  | Touches: 2 | Distance: 5.4%\n","  ₹1415.46 – ₹1427.40  | Touches: 4 | Distance: 9.7%\n","  ₹1466.22 – ₹1482.64  | Touches: 3 | Distance: 13.8%\n","  ₹1573.62 – ₹1574.02  | Touches: 2 | Distance: 21.5%\n"]},{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<Figure size 1600x800 with 1 Axes>"],"image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}},{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["\n","Chart saved as stage3_support_resistance.png\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["import yfinance as yf\n","import pandas as pd\n","import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n","\n","# --- Step 1: Download data ---\n","ticker = yf.Ticker(\"RELIANCE.NS\")\n","df = ticker.history(period=\"2y\", interval=\"1d\")\n","df = df[['Open','High','Low','Close','Volume']].copy()\n","df.reset_index(inplace=True)\n","\n","prices = df['Close'].tolist()\n","print(f\"Total trading days loaded: {len(prices)}\")\n","\n","# --- Step 2: Build EMA from pure math (no pandas/ta-lib) ---\n","\n","def calculate_ema(prices, period):\n","    \"\"\"\n","    Calculates EMA using pure math.\n","    No libraries used — just the recursive formula.\n","\n","    Initialization: Use the SMA of the first 'period' days\n","    as the seed value. This is the professional standard.\n","    (Seeding with just the first price introduces early error.)\n","    \"\"\"\n","    if len(prices) < period:\n","        print(f\"Not enough data for EMA-{period}\")\n","        return []\n","\n","    alpha = 2 / (period + 1)\n","\n","    # Step 1: Seed with SMA of first 'period' prices\n","    first_sma = sum(prices[:period]) / period\n","    ema_values = [None] * (period - 1)  # no EMA before enough data\n","    ema_values.append(first_sma)        # first real EMA value\n","\n","    # Step 2: Apply recursive formula for all remaining prices\n","    for i in range(period, len(prices)):\n","        new_ema = alpha * prices[i] + (1 - alpha) * ema_values[-1]\n","        ema_values.append(new_ema)\n","\n","    return ema_values\n","\n","# Calculate both EMAs\n","ema_50  = calculate_ema(prices, 50)\n","ema_200 = calculate_ema(prices, 200)\n","\n","print(f\"EMA-50  calculated: {len([x for x in ema_50  if x])} values\")\n","print(f\"EMA-200 calculated: {len([x for x in ema_200 if x])} values\")\n","\n","# Add to dataframe\n","df['EMA_50']  = ema_50\n","df['EMA_200'] = ema_200\n","\n","# --- Step 3: Trend classification ---\n","def classify_trend(row):\n","    \"\"\"\n","    Uses both EMAs to classify market regime.\n","    Matches exactly what Slide 9 describes.\n","    \"\"\"\n","    if pd.isna(row['EMA_50']) or pd.isna(row['EMA_200']):\n","        return 'insufficient_data'\n","    elif row['Close'] > row['EMA_50'] > row['EMA_200']:\n","        return 'strong_uptrend'      # Price > 50 EMA > 200 EMA\n","    elif row['Close'] > row['EMA_200'] and row['EMA_50'] > row['EMA_200']:\n","        return 'uptrend'             # Above 200, structure intact\n","    elif row['Close'] < row['EMA_50'] < row['EMA_200']:\n","        return 'strong_downtrend'    # Price < 50 EMA < 200 EMA\n","    elif row['Close'] < row['EMA_200'] and row['EMA_50'] < row['EMA_200']:\n","        return 'downtrend'           # Below 200, bearish structure\n","    else:\n","        return 'ranging'             # Mixed — no clear regime\n","\n","df['trend'] = df.apply(classify_trend, axis=1)\n","\n","# Current state\n","latest = df.iloc[-1]\n","print(f\"\\n=== Current Market State ===\")\n","print(f\"Date         : {latest['Date'].date()}\")\n","print(f\"Close Price  : ₹{latest['Close']:.2f}\")\n","print(f\"EMA-50       : ₹{latest['EMA_50']:.2f}\")\n","print(f\"EMA-200      : ₹{latest['EMA_200']:.2f}\")\n","print(f\"Trend regime : {latest['trend'].upper()}\")\n","\n","# Alpha values\n","alpha_50  = 2 / (50  + 1)\n","alpha_200 = 2 / (200 + 1)\n","print(f\"\\n=== Alpha Values ===\")\n","print(f\"α for EMA-50  = 2/(50+1)  = {alpha_50:.6f}\")\n","print(f\"α for EMA-200 = 2/(200+1) = {alpha_200:.6f}\")\n","print(f\"EMA-50 reacts {alpha_50/alpha_200:.1f}x faster than EMA-200\")\n","\n","# --- Step 4: Verify against pandas (sanity check) ---\n","pd_ema_50  = df['Close'].ewm(span=50,  adjust=False).mean()\n","pd_ema_200 = df['Close'].ewm(span=200, adjust=False).mean()\n","\n","our_last   = df['EMA_50'].iloc[-1]\n","pd_last    = pd_ema_50.iloc[-1]\n","print(f\"\\n=== Sanity Check (our EMA vs pandas EMA) ===\")\n","print(f\"Our EMA-50 (last value)    : ₹{our_last:.4f}\")\n","print(f\"Pandas EMA-50 (last value) : ₹{pd_last:.4f}\")\n","print(f\"Difference                 : ₹{abs(our_last - pd_last):.4f}\")\n","print(\"(Small difference due to different seeding method — both correct)\")\n","\n","# --- Step 5: Visualize ---\n","fig, (ax1, ax2) = plt.subplots(2, 1, figsize=(16, 9),\n","                                gridspec_kw={'height_ratios': [3, 1]})\n","\n","# Price + EMAs\n","ax1.plot(df.index, df['Close'],\n","         color='gray', linewidth=0.8, alpha=0.7, label='Close Price')\n","ax1.plot(df.index, df['EMA_50'],\n","         color='steelblue', linewidth=1.8, label='50-Day EMA (Swing Trend)')\n","ax1.plot(df.index, df['EMA_200'],\n","         color='darkorange', linewidth=2.2, label='200-Day EMA (Institutional Bias)')\n","\n","# Shade trend regions\n","for i in range(1, len(df)):\n","    if pd.notna(df['EMA_50'].iloc[i]) and pd.notna(df['EMA_200'].iloc[i]):\n","        if df['EMA_50'].iloc[i] > df['EMA_200'].iloc[i]:\n","            ax1.axvspan(df.index[i-1], df.index[i],\n","                        alpha=0.05, color='green')\n","        else:\n","            ax1.axvspan(df.index[i-1], df.index[i],\n","                        alpha=0.05, color='red')\n","\n","ax1.set_title('Reliance Industries — 50 & 200 Day EMA '\n","              '(Green = Bullish Regime, Red = Bearish Regime)', fontsize=13)\n","ax1.set_ylabel('Price (₹)')\n","ax1.legend(loc='upper left')\n","\n","# EMA gap (distance between 50 and 200)\n","valid = df.dropna(subset=['EMA_50','EMA_200'])\n","gap   = valid['EMA_50'] - valid['EMA_200']\n","colors = ['green' if g > 0 else 'red' for g in gap]\n","ax2.bar(valid.index, gap, color=colors, alpha=0.6, width=1)\n","ax2.axhline(y=0, color='black', linewidth=1)\n","ax2.set_ylabel('EMA Gap (50 - 200)')\n","ax2.set_title('EMA Gap — positive = bullish structure, negative = bearish')\n","\n","plt.tight_layout()\n","plt.savefig('stage4_ema.png', dpi=150)\n","plt.show()\n","print(\"\\nChart saved as stage4_ema.png\")"],"metadata":{"id":"1YBKIVvHfZ7J","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1780641416940,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":4831,"user":{"displayName":"","userId":""}},"outputId":"ee7f1338-330b-43b6-973e-87b9b9917e98","colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":995}},"execution_count":13,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Total trading days loaded: 498\n","EMA-50  calculated: 449 values\n","EMA-200 calculated: 299 values\n","\n","=== Current Market State ===\n","Date         : 2026-06-05\n","Close Price  : ₹1295.10\n","EMA-50       : ₹1358.36\n","EMA-200      : ₹1399.77\n","Trend regime : STRONG_DOWNTREND\n","\n","=== Alpha Values ===\n","α for EMA-50  = 2/(50+1)  = 0.039216\n","α for EMA-200 = 2/(200+1) = 0.009950\n","EMA-50 reacts 3.9x faster than EMA-200\n","\n","=== Sanity Check (our EMA vs pandas EMA) ===\n","Our EMA-50 (last value)    : ₹1358.3640\n","Pandas EMA-50 (last value) : ₹1358.3640\n","Difference                 : ₹0.0000\n","(Small difference due to different seeding method — both correct)\n"]},{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<Figure size 1600x900 with 2 Axes>"],"image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}},{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["\n","Chart saved as stage4_ema.png\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["import yfinance as yf\n","import pandas as pd\n","import numpy as np\n","import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n","\n","# --- Step 1: Download data ---\n","ticker = yf.Ticker(\"RELIANCE.NS\")\n","df = ticker.history(period=\"3y\", interval=\"1d\")\n","df = df[['Open','High','Low','Close','Volume']].copy()\n","df.reset_index(inplace=True)\n","\n","prices = df['Close'].tolist()\n","\n","# --- Step 2: Reuse our pure-math EMA from Stage 4 ---\n","def calculate_ema(prices, period):\n","    if len(prices) < period:\n","        return [None] * len(prices)\n","    alpha = 2 / (period + 1)\n","    first_sma = sum(prices[:period]) / period\n","    ema_values = [None] * (period - 1)\n","    ema_values.append(first_sma)\n","    for i in range(period, len(prices)):\n","        new_ema = alpha * prices[i] + (1 - alpha) * ema_values[-1]\n","        ema_values.append(new_ema)\n","    return ema_values\n","\n","df['EMA_50']  = calculate_ema(prices, 50)\n","df['EMA_200'] = calculate_ema(prices, 200)\n","\n","# --- Step 3: Calculate volume averages for confirmation ---\n","# 1-month volume average  ≈ 21 trading days\n","# 1-year volume average   ≈ 252 trading days\n","\n","df['vol_1month'] = df['Volume'].rolling(window=21).mean()\n","df['vol_1year']  = df['Volume'].rolling(window=252).mean()\n","\n","# Volume confirmation: today's 1-month avg > 1-year avg\n","df['volume_confirmed'] = df['vol_1month'] > df['vol_1year']\n","\n","# --- Step 4: Detect crossover events ---\n","crossovers = []\n","\n","for i in range(1, len(df)):\n","    prev = df.iloc[i-1]\n","    curr = df.iloc[i]\n","\n","    # Skip rows without full EMA data\n","    if any(pd.isna([prev['EMA_50'], prev['EMA_200'],\n","                    curr['EMA_50'],  curr['EMA_200']])):\n","        continue\n","\n","    prev_diff = prev['EMA_50'] - prev['EMA_200']\n","    curr_diff = curr['EMA_50'] - curr['EMA_200']\n","\n","    # Golden Cross: diff crosses from negative to positive\n","    if prev_diff < 0 and curr_diff > 0:\n","        vol_confirmed = curr['volume_confirmed']\n","        crossovers.append({\n","            'date'         : curr['Date'],\n","            'index'        : i,\n","            'type'         : 'GOLDEN CROSS',\n","            'price'        : curr['Close'],\n","            'ema_50'       : curr['EMA_50'],\n","            'ema_200'      : curr['EMA_200'],\n","            'vol_confirmed': vol_confirmed,\n","            'signal'       : 'BUY' if vol_confirmed else 'WEAK BUY'\n","        })\n","\n","    # Death Cross: diff crosses from positive to negative\n","    elif prev_diff > 0 and curr_diff < 0:\n","        vol_confirmed = curr['volume_confirmed']\n","        crossovers.append({\n","            'date'         : curr['Date'],\n","            'index'        : i,\n","            'type'         : 'DEATH CROSS',\n","            'price'        : curr['Close'],\n","            'ema_50'       : curr['EMA_50'],\n","            'ema_200'      : curr['EMA_200'],\n","            'vol_confirmed': vol_confirmed,\n","            'signal'       : 'SELL' if vol_confirmed else 'WEAK SELL'\n","        })\n","\n","# --- Step 5: Print crossover report ---\n","print(\"=\" * 65)\n","print(\"  CROSSOVER SCANNER REPORT — RELIANCE INDUSTRIES\")\n","print(\"=\" * 65)\n","\n","if not crossovers:\n","    print(\"No crossovers found in this period.\")\n","else:\n","    for c in crossovers:\n","        icon = \"★\" if c['type'] == 'GOLDEN CROSS' else \"▼\"\n","        vol  = \"✓ VOL CONFIRMED\" if c['vol_confirmed'] else \"✗ LOW VOLUME\"\n","        print(f\"\\n{icon} {c['type']}\")\n","        print(f\"  Date      : {c['date'].date()}\")\n","        print(f\"  Price     : ₹{c['price']:.2f}\")\n","        print(f\"  EMA-50    : ₹{c['ema_50']:.2f}\")\n","        print(f\"  EMA-200   : ₹{c['ema_200']:.2f}\")\n","        print(f\"  Volume    : {vol}\")\n","        print(f\"  Signal    : {c['signal']}\")\n","\n","# --- Step 6: Current regime ---\n","latest = df.dropna(subset=['EMA_50','EMA_200']).iloc[-1]\n","gap    = latest['EMA_50'] - latest['EMA_200']\n","regime = \"BULLISH (Golden Cross active)\" if gap > 0 \\\n","         else \"BEARISH (Death Cross active)\"\n","\n","print(f\"\\n{'='*65}\")\n","print(f\"  CURRENT REGIME: {regime}\")\n","print(f\"  EMA-50  : ₹{latest['EMA_50']:.2f}\")\n","print(f\"  EMA-200 : ₹{latest['EMA_200']:.2f}\")\n","print(f\"  EMA Gap : ₹{gap:.2f}\")\n","print(f\"{'='*65}\")\n","\n","# --- Step 7: Visualize ---\n","fig, (ax1, ax2, ax3) = plt.subplots(\n","    3, 1, figsize=(16, 12),\n","    gridspec_kw={'height_ratios': [3, 1, 1]}\n",")\n","\n","# Price + EMAs\n","ax1.plot(df.index, df['Close'],\n","         color='gray', linewidth=0.8, alpha=0.6, label='Close')\n","ax1.plot(df.index, df['EMA_50'],\n","         color='steelblue', linewidth=1.8, label='EMA-50 (Swing)')\n","ax1.plot(df.index, df['EMA_200'],\n","         color='darkorange', linewidth=2.2, label='EMA-200 (Institutional)')\n","\n","# Mark crossover events on price chart\n","for c in crossovers:\n","    idx   = c['index']\n","    color = 'gold' if c['type'] == 'GOLDEN CROSS' else 'black'\n","    marker= '^' if c['type'] == 'GOLDEN CROSS' else 'v'\n","    size  = 150 if c['vol_confirmed'] else 60\n","    ax1.scatter(idx, c['price'], color=color,\n","                marker=marker, s=size, zorder=6)\n","    ax1.annotate(\n","        'GC' if c['type'] == 'GOLDEN CROSS' else 'DC',\n","        xy=(idx, c['price']),\n","        xytext=(idx, c['price'] * 1.03),\n","        fontsize=7, ha='center',\n","        color=color\n","    )\n","\n","# Shade bullish/bearish regimes\n","valid = df.dropna(subset=['EMA_50','EMA_200'])\n","for i in range(1, len(valid)):\n","    gap = valid['EMA_50'].iloc[i] - valid['EMA_200'].iloc[i]\n","    color = 'green' if gap > 0 else 'red'\n","    ax1.axvspan(valid.index[i-1], valid.index[i],\n","                alpha=0.04, color=color)\n","\n","ax1.set_title('Golden Cross / Death Cross Scanner — '\n","              'Large markers = volume confirmed', fontsize=12)\n","ax1.set_ylabel('Price (₹)')\n","ax1.legend(loc='upper left')\n","\n","# EMA gap\n","gap_series = df['EMA_50'] - df['EMA_200']\n","gap_colors = ['green' if g > 0 else 'red'\n","              for g in gap_series.fillna(0)]\n","ax2.bar(df.index, gap_series, color=gap_colors, alpha=0.6, width=1)\n","ax2.axhline(y=0, color='black', linewidth=1.2)\n","ax2.set_ylabel('EMA Gap')\n","ax2.set_title('EMA Gap (50 - 200): crossing zero = crossover event')\n","\n","# Volume with moving averages\n","ax3.bar(df.index, df['Volume']/1e6,\n","        color='steelblue', alpha=0.4, width=1, label='Daily Volume')\n","ax3.plot(df.index, df['vol_1month']/1e6,\n","         color='orange', linewidth=1.2, label='1-Month Avg')\n","ax3.plot(df.index, df['vol_1year']/1e6,\n","         color='red', linewidth=1.5, label='1-Year Avg')\n","ax3.set_ylabel('Volume (M)')\n","ax3.set_title('Volume — orange above red = volume confirmation active')\n","ax3.legend(loc='upper left')\n","\n","plt.tight_layout()\n","plt.savefig('stage5_crossover.png', dpi=150)\n","plt.show()\n","print(\"\\nChart saved as stage5_crossover.png\")"],"metadata":{"id":"DMC3dYa3gQ-L","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1780641538685,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":6582,"user":{"displayName":"","userId":""}},"outputId":"064d7d07-f8d3-4d4b-c1f7-8ec47a29dd9f","colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":1000}},"execution_count":14,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["=================================================================\n","  CROSSOVER SCANNER REPORT — RELIANCE INDUSTRIES\n","=================================================================\n","\n","▼ DEATH CROSS\n","  Date      : 2024-11-01\n","  Price     : ₹1327.19\n","  EMA-50    : ₹1396.97\n","  EMA-200   : ₹1397.53\n","  Volume    : ✓ VOL CONFIRMED\n","  Signal    : SELL\n","\n","★ GOLDEN CROSS\n","  Date      : 2025-05-15\n","  Price     : ₹1441.75\n","  EMA-50    : ₹1306.18\n","  EMA-200   : ₹1302.30\n","  Volume    : ✓ VOL CONFIRMED\n","  Signal    : BUY\n","\n","▼ DEATH CROSS\n","  Date      : 2026-03-12\n","  Price     : ₹1385.79\n","  EMA-50    : ₹1426.75\n","  EMA-200   : ₹1426.96\n","  Volume    : ✓ VOL CONFIRMED\n","  Signal    : SELL\n","\n","=================================================================\n","  CURRENT REGIME: BEARISH (Death Cross active)\n","  EMA-50  : ₹1358.36\n","  EMA-200 : ₹1397.04\n","  EMA Gap : ₹-38.67\n","=================================================================\n"]},{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<Figure size 1600x1200 with 3 Axes>"],"image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}},{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["\n","Chart saved as stage5_crossover.png\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["import yfinance as yf\n","import pandas as pd\n","import numpy as np\n","import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n","import matplotlib.gridspec as gridspec\n","\n","# --- Step 1: Download data ---\n","ticker = yf.Ticker(\"RELIANCE.NS\")\n","df = ticker.history(period=\"2y\", interval=\"1d\")\n","df = df[['Open','High','Low','Close','Volume']].copy()\n","df.reset_index(inplace=True)\n","\n","prices = df['Close'].tolist()\n","\n","# --- Step 2: Pure-math EMA (reused from Stage 4) ---\n","def calculate_ema(prices, period):\n","    if len(prices) < period:\n","        return [None] * len(prices)\n","    alpha = 2 / (period + 1)\n","    first_sma = sum(prices[:period]) / period\n","    ema_values = [None] * (period - 1)\n","    ema_values.append(first_sma)\n","    for i in range(period, len(prices)):\n","        new_ema = alpha * prices[i] + (1 - alpha) * ema_values[-1]\n","        ema_values.append(new_ema)\n","    return ema_values\n","\n","df['EMA_50']  = calculate_ema(prices, 50)\n","df['EMA_200'] = calculate_ema(prices, 200)\n","\n","# --- Step 3: Wilder's RSI — pure math, no libraries ---\n","def calculate_rsi_wilder(prices, period=14):\n","    \"\"\"\n","    Implements J. Welles Wilder's original RSI formula exactly.\n","    Period 14 is the standard Wilder used in his 1978 book.\n","    \"\"\"\n","    rsi_values = [None] * len(prices)\n","\n","    if len(prices) < period + 1:\n","        return rsi_values\n","\n","    # Step 1: Calculate all daily changes\n","    changes = []\n","    for i in range(1, len(prices)):\n","        changes.append(prices[i] - prices[i-1])\n","\n","    # Step 2: Separate into gains and losses\n","    gains  = [max(c, 0) for c in changes]\n","    losses = [abs(min(c, 0)) for c in changes]\n","\n","    # Step 3: First average (simple average of first 14)\n","    avg_gain = sum(gains[:period]) / period\n","    avg_loss = sum(losses[:period]) / period\n","\n","    # Step 4: First RSI value\n","    if avg_loss == 0:\n","        rsi_values[period] = 100.0\n","    else:\n","        rs  = avg_gain / avg_loss\n","        rsi_values[period] = round(100 - (100 / (1 + rs)), 4)\n","\n","    # Step 5: Wilder smoothing for remaining values\n","    for i in range(period, len(changes)):\n","        avg_gain = (avg_gain * (period - 1) + gains[i])  / period\n","        avg_loss = (avg_loss * (period - 1) + losses[i]) / period\n","\n","        if avg_loss == 0:\n","            rsi_values[i + 1] = 100.0\n","        else:\n","            rs  = avg_gain / avg_loss\n","            rsi_values[i + 1] = round(100 - (100 / (1 + rs)), 4)\n","\n","    return rsi_values\n","\n","df['RSI'] = calculate_rsi_wilder(prices, period=14)\n","\n","# --- Step 4: Detect RSI crossovers of the 50 line ---\n","df['rsi_above_50'] = df['RSI'].apply(\n","    lambda x: x > 50 if x is not None else None\n",")\n","\n","# --- Step 5: Apply the Confluence Rule from Slide 11 ---\n","def confluence_signal(row):\n","    \"\"\"\n","    Gate B: EMA structure aligned (50 > 200)\n","    Gate C: RSI confirming momentum > 50\n","    Both gates pass → EXECUTE\n","    Either fails    → IDLE\n","    \"\"\"\n","    if pd.isna(row['EMA_50']) or pd.isna(row['EMA_200']) \\\n","       or pd.isna(row['RSI']):\n","        return 'NO_DATA'\n","\n","    ema_aligned = row['EMA_50'] > row['EMA_200']   # Gate B\n","    rsi_confirm = row['RSI'] > 50                   # Gate C\n","\n","    if ema_aligned and rsi_confirm:\n","        return 'EXECUTE'       # Both gates pass\n","    elif ema_aligned and not rsi_confirm:\n","        return 'WAIT_RSI'      # Structure good, momentum lagging\n","    elif not ema_aligned and rsi_confirm:\n","        return 'WAIT_EMA'      # Momentum there, structure not yet\n","    else:\n","        return 'IDLE'          # Both failing — stay out\n","\n","df['confluence'] = df.apply(confluence_signal, axis=1)\n","\n","# --- Step 6: Print current state ---\n","latest = df.dropna(subset=['EMA_50','EMA_200','RSI']).iloc[-1]\n","\n","print(\"=\" * 60)\n","print(\"  RSI + CONFLUENCE ANALYSIS — RELIANCE INDUSTRIES\")\n","print(\"=\" * 60)\n","print(f\"  Date         : {latest['Date'].date()}\")\n","print(f\"  Close        : ₹{latest['Close']:.2f}\")\n","print(f\"  EMA-50       : ₹{latest['EMA_50']:.2f}\")\n","print(f\"  EMA-200      : ₹{latest['EMA_200']:.2f}\")\n","print(f\"  RSI (14)     : {latest['RSI']:.2f}\")\n","print(f\"  Gate B (EMA) : {'PASS' if latest['EMA_50'] > latest['EMA_200'] else 'FAIL'}\")\n","print(f\"  Gate C (RSI) : {'PASS' if latest['RSI'] > 50 else 'FAIL'}\")\n","print(f\"  Confluence   : {latest['confluence']}\")\n","print(\"=\" * 60)\n","\n","# RSI distribution analysis\n","valid_rsi = df['RSI'].dropna()\n","print(f\"\\n  RSI Statistics (last {len(valid_rsi)} days):\")\n","print(f\"  Current  : {latest['RSI']:.2f}\")\n","print(f\"  Average  : {valid_rsi.mean():.2f}\")\n","print(f\"  Max      : {valid_rsi.max():.2f}\")\n","print(f\"  Min      : {valid_rsi.min():.2f}\")\n","print(f\"  Days above 70 (overbought) : {(valid_rsi > 70).sum()}\")\n","print(f\"  Days below 30 (oversold)   : {(valid_rsi < 30).sum()}\")\n","print(f\"  Days above 50 (bullish)    : {(valid_rsi > 50).sum()}\")\n","\n","# Count confluence states\n","print(f\"\\n  Confluence State Distribution:\")\n","for state in ['EXECUTE','WAIT_RSI','WAIT_EMA','IDLE']:\n","    count = (df['confluence'] == state).sum()\n","    pct   = count / len(df) * 100\n","    print(f\"  {state:<12}: {count:>4} days ({pct:.1f}%)\")\n","\n","# --- Step 7: Visualize ---\n","fig = plt.figure(figsize=(16, 12))\n","gs  = gridspec.GridSpec(3, 1, height_ratios=[3, 1.5, 1])\n","\n","ax1 = fig.add_subplot(gs[0])\n","ax2 = fig.add_subplot(gs[1], sharex=ax1)\n","ax3 = fig.add_subplot(gs[2], sharex=ax1)\n","\n","# Price chart with confluence shading\n","execute_color = {'EXECUTE': 'green', 'WAIT_RSI': 'yellow',\n","                 'WAIT_EMA': 'orange', 'IDLE': 'red', 'NO_DATA': 'gray'}\n","\n","for i in range(1, len(df)):\n","    state = df['confluence'].iloc[i]\n","    color = execute_color.get(state, 'gray')\n","    ax1.axvspan(df.index[i-1], df.index[i],\n","                alpha=0.08, color=color)\n","\n","ax1.plot(df.index, df['Close'],\n","         color='black', linewidth=0.9, label='Close', zorder=3)\n","ax1.plot(df.index, df['EMA_50'],\n","         color='steelblue', linewidth=1.8, label='EMA-50')\n","ax1.plot(df.index, df['EMA_200'],\n","         color='darkorange', linewidth=2.2, label='EMA-200')\n","\n","ax1.set_title('Price + EMA Structure  |  '\n","              'Green=EXECUTE  Yellow=WAIT_RSI  '\n","              'Orange=WAIT_EMA  Red=IDLE', fontsize=11)\n","ax1.set_ylabel('Price (₹)')\n","ax1.legend(loc='upper left', fontsize=9)\n","\n","# RSI chart\n","ax2.plot(df.index, df['RSI'],\n","         color='purple', linewidth=1.4, label='RSI (14)')\n","ax2.axhline(y=70, color='red',    linestyle='--',\n","            linewidth=1, alpha=0.7, label='Overbought (70)')\n","ax2.axhline(y=50, color='black',  linestyle='-',\n","            linewidth=1.2, label='Neutral (50)')\n","ax2.axhline(y=30, color='green',  linestyle='--',\n","            linewidth=1, alpha=0.7, label='Oversold (30)')\n","\n","# Shade RSI zones\n","ax2.fill_between(df.index, df['RSI'], 50,\n","                 where=df['RSI'] > 50,\n","                 alpha=0.15, color='green', label='Bullish momentum')\n","ax2.fill_between(df.index, df['RSI'], 50,\n","                 where=df['RSI'] < 50,\n","                 alpha=0.15, color='red', label='Bearish momentum')\n","\n","ax2.set_ylabel('RSI')\n","ax2.set_ylim(0, 100)\n","ax2.legend(loc='upper left', fontsize=8, ncol=3)\n","ax2.set_title('RSI (14) — Wilder Method  |  '\n","              'Key level: 50 threshold', fontsize=11)\n","\n","# Confluence state bar\n","confluence_map = {'EXECUTE': 3, 'WAIT_RSI': 2,\n","                  'WAIT_EMA': 1, 'IDLE': 0, 'NO_DATA': -1}\n","conf_numeric = df['confluence'].map(confluence_map)\n","conf_colors  = df['confluence'].map(execute_color)\n","\n","ax3.bar(df.index, conf_numeric,\n","        color=conf_colors, alpha=0.7, width=1)\n","ax3.set_yticks([0, 1, 2, 3])\n","ax3.set_yticklabels(['IDLE', 'WAIT_EMA', 'WAIT_RSI', 'EXECUTE'],\n","                    fontsize=8)\n","ax3.set_title('IPO Engine State (Gates B + C only)', fontsize=11)\n","\n","plt.tight_layout()\n","plt.savefig('stage6_rsi_confluence.png', dpi=150)\n","plt.show()\n","print(\"\\nChart saved as stage6_rsi_confluence.png\")"],"metadata":{"id":"FCMfNQsAh1sU","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1780641945038,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":6170,"user":{"displayName":"","userId":""}},"outputId":"607f6387-185b-41d7-e022-dec3eb520244","colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":1000}},"execution_count":15,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["============================================================\n","  RSI + CONFLUENCE ANALYSIS — RELIANCE INDUSTRIES\n","============================================================\n","  Date         : 2026-06-05\n","  Close        : ₹1296.60\n","  EMA-50       : ₹1358.42\n","  EMA-200      : ₹1399.79\n","  RSI (14)     : 34.47\n","  Gate B (EMA) : FAIL\n","  Gate C (RSI) : FAIL\n","  Confluence   : IDLE\n","============================================================\n","\n","  RSI Statistics (last 484 days):\n","  Current  : 34.47\n","  Average  : 49.66\n","  Max      : 79.27\n","  Min      : 23.93\n","  Days above 70 (overbought) : 36\n","  Days below 30 (oversold)   : 20\n","  Days above 50 (bullish)    : 223\n","\n","  Confluence State Distribution:\n","  EXECUTE     :  102 days (20.5%)\n","  WAIT_RSI    :   86 days (17.3%)\n","  WAIT_EMA    :   56 days (11.2%)\n","  IDLE        :   55 days (11.0%)\n"]},{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<Figure size 1600x1200 with 3 Axes>"],"image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}},{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["\n","Chart saved as stage6_rsi_confluence.png\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["import yfinance as yf\n","import pandas as pd\n","import numpy as np\n","import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n","import matplotlib.gridspec as gridspec\n","from datetime import datetime\n","\n","print(\"=\" * 65)\n","print(\"   IPO DECISION ENGINE — COMPLETE PIPELINE\")\n","print(\"   DecodeLabs Project 1 — Systematic Trading System\")\n","print(\"=\" * 65)\n","\n","# ============================================================\n","# CONFIGURATION — tune these parameters\n","# ============================================================\n","TICKER          = \"RELIANCE.NS\"\n","PERIOD          = \"2y\"\n","INTERVAL        = \"1d\"\n","\n","RWB_THRESHOLD   = 2.0    # Gate A: minimum R_wb for rejection signal\n","ZONE_TOLERANCE  = 0.015  # Gate A: zone width (1.5% of price)\n","ZONE_PROXIMITY  = 0.02   # Gate A: how close to zone (2%)\n","SWING_LOOKBACK  = 5      # Gate A: swing point detection window\n","RSI_PERIOD      = 14     # Gate C: RSI period (Wilder standard)\n","RSI_THRESHOLD   = 50     # Gate C: minimum RSI for Gate C pass\n","VOL_SHORT       = 21     # Gate B: 1-month volume window\n","VOL_LONG        = 252    # Gate B: 1-year volume window\n","\n","# ============================================================\n","# MODULE 1 — DATA LOADING\n","# ============================================================\n","print(\"\\n[1/6] Loading market data...\")\n","ticker_obj = yf.Ticker(TICKER)\n","df = ticker_obj.history(period=PERIOD, interval=INTERVAL)\n","df = df[['Open','High','Low','Close','Volume']].copy()\n","df.reset_index(inplace=True)\n","prices = df['Close'].tolist()\n","print(f\"      Loaded {len(df)} trading days for {TICKER}\")\n","\n","# ============================================================\n","# MODULE 2 — INDICATOR CALCULATIONS\n","# ============================================================\n","print(\"\\n[2/6] Calculating indicators...\")\n","\n","# --- EMA (pure math from Stage 4) ---\n","def calculate_ema(prices, period):\n","    if len(prices) < period:\n","        return [None] * len(prices)\n","    alpha = 2 / (period + 1)\n","    first_sma = sum(prices[:period]) / period\n","    ema_values = [None] * (period - 1)\n","    ema_values.append(first_sma)\n","    for i in range(period, len(prices)):\n","        new_ema = alpha * prices[i] + (1 - alpha) * ema_values[-1]\n","        ema_values.append(new_ema)\n","    return ema_values\n","\n","# --- RSI Wilder (pure math from Stage 6) ---\n","def calculate_rsi(prices, period=14):\n","    rsi_values = [None] * len(prices)\n","    if len(prices) < period + 1:\n","        return rsi_values\n","    changes = [prices[i] - prices[i-1] for i in range(1, len(prices))]\n","    gains   = [max(c, 0)    for c in changes]\n","    losses  = [abs(min(c, 0)) for c in changes]\n","    avg_gain = sum(gains[:period])  / period\n","    avg_loss = sum(losses[:period]) / period\n","    if avg_loss == 0:\n","        rsi_values[period] = 100.0\n","    else:\n","        rsi_values[period] = round(\n","            100 - (100 / (1 + avg_gain / avg_loss)), 4\n","        )\n","    for i in range(period, len(changes)):\n","        avg_gain = (avg_gain * (period-1) + gains[i])  / period\n","        avg_loss = (avg_loss * (period-1) + losses[i]) / period\n","        if avg_loss == 0:\n","            rsi_values[i+1] = 100.0\n","        else:\n","            rsi_values[i+1] = round(\n","                100 - (100 / (1 + avg_gain / avg_loss)), 4\n","            )\n","    return rsi_values\n","\n","# --- R_wb (pure math from Stage 2) ---\n","def calculate_rwb(row):\n","    upper_wick = row['High'] - max(row['Open'], row['Close'])\n","    lower_wick = min(row['Open'], row['Close']) - row['Low']\n","    body       = abs(row['Open'] - row['Close'])\n","    if body == 0:\n","        return None\n","    return round((upper_wick + lower_wick) / body, 4)\n","\n","# Apply all indicators\n","df['EMA_50']  = calculate_ema(prices, 50)\n","df['EMA_200'] = calculate_ema(prices, 200)\n","df['RSI']     = calculate_rsi(prices, RSI_PERIOD)\n","df['R_wb']    = df.apply(calculate_rwb, axis=1)\n","df['vol_1m']  = df['Volume'].rolling(VOL_SHORT).mean()\n","df['vol_1yr'] = df['Volume'].rolling(VOL_LONG).mean()\n","\n","print(f\"      EMA-50, EMA-200, RSI-{RSI_PERIOD}, R_wb, Volume MAs computed\")\n","\n","# ============================================================\n","# MODULE 3 — SUPPORT & RESISTANCE ZONES (from Stage 3)\n","# ============================================================\n","print(\"\\n[3/6] Mapping support & resistance zones...\")\n","\n","def find_swing_points(df, lookback=5):\n","    swing_highs, swing_lows = [], []\n","    for i in range(lookback, len(df) - lookback):\n","        hi_window = df['High'][i-lookback : i+lookback+1]\n","        lo_window = df['Low'][i-lookback  : i+lookback+1]\n","        if df['High'][i] == hi_window.max():\n","            swing_highs.append(i)\n","        if df['Low'][i] == lo_window.min():\n","            swing_lows.append(i)\n","    return swing_highs, swing_lows\n","\n","def cluster_zones(indices, prices, tolerance=0.015):\n","    levels = sorted([prices[i] for i in indices])\n","    zones, used = [], [False] * len(levels)\n","    for i in range(len(levels)):\n","        if used[i]:\n","            continue\n","        cluster = [levels[i]]\n","        used[i] = True\n","        for j in range(i+1, len(levels)):\n","            if not used[j]:\n","                if abs(levels[j] - np.mean(cluster)) \\\n","                   / np.mean(cluster) < tolerance:\n","                    cluster.append(levels[j])\n","                    used[j] = True\n","        zones.append({\n","            'low'     : min(cluster),\n","            'high'    : max(cluster),\n","            'mid'     : np.mean(cluster),\n","            'strength': len(cluster)\n","        })\n","    return [z for z in zones if z['strength'] >= 2]\n","\n","sh_idx, sl_idx = find_swing_points(df, SWING_LOOKBACK)\n","resistance_zones = cluster_zones(sh_idx, df['High'].values, ZONE_TOLERANCE)\n","support_zones    = cluster_zones(sl_idx, df['Low'].values,  ZONE_TOLERANCE)\n","\n","print(f\"      Support zones: {len(support_zones)} | \"\n","      f\"Resistance zones: {len(resistance_zones)}\")\n","\n","# ============================================================\n","# MODULE 4 — THREE GATE EVALUATION\n","# ============================================================\n","print(\"\\n[4/6] Running three-gate evaluation...\")\n","\n","def evaluate_gates(row, support_zones, resistance_zones):\n","    \"\"\"\n","    Evaluates all three gates for a single row.\n","    Returns detailed gate results + final engine decision.\n","    \"\"\"\n","    result = {\n","        'gate_a_zone'  : False,\n","        'gate_a_rwb'   : False,\n","        'gate_a'       : False,\n","        'gate_b_ema'   : False,\n","        'gate_b_vol'   : False,\n","        'gate_b'       : False,\n","        'gate_c'       : False,\n","        'zone_type'    : None,\n","        'zone_mid'     : None,\n","        'decision'     : 'IDLE'\n","    }\n","\n","    # Skip if insufficient data\n","    if pd.isna(row['EMA_50']) or pd.isna(row['EMA_200']) \\\n","       or pd.isna(row['RSI']) or pd.isna(row['R_wb']):\n","        return result\n","\n","    price = row['Close']\n","\n","    # ── GATE A: Structure ─────────────────────────────────\n","    # Check if price is near any support or resistance zone\n","    at_zone   = False\n","    zone_type = None\n","    zone_mid  = None\n","\n","    for zone in support_zones:\n","        dist_pct = abs(price - zone['mid']) / price\n","        if dist_pct < ZONE_PROXIMITY:\n","            at_zone   = True\n","            zone_type = 'SUPPORT'\n","            zone_mid  = zone['mid']\n","            break\n","\n","    if not at_zone:\n","        for zone in resistance_zones:\n","            dist_pct = abs(price - zone['mid']) / price\n","            if dist_pct < ZONE_PROXIMITY:\n","                at_zone   = True\n","                zone_type = 'RESISTANCE'\n","                zone_mid  = zone['mid']\n","                break\n","\n","    result['gate_a_zone'] = at_zone\n","    result['gate_a_rwb']  = (row['R_wb'] is not None\n","                             and row['R_wb'] > RWB_THRESHOLD)\n","    result['gate_a']      = result['gate_a_zone'] \\\n","                            and result['gate_a_rwb']\n","    result['zone_type']   = zone_type\n","    result['zone_mid']    = zone_mid\n","\n","    # ── GATE B: Trend ─────────────────────────────────────\n","    result['gate_b_ema'] = row['EMA_50'] > row['EMA_200']\n","    result['gate_b_vol'] = (not pd.isna(row['vol_1m'])\n","                            and not pd.isna(row['vol_1yr'])\n","                            and row['vol_1m'] > row['vol_1yr'])\n","    result['gate_b']     = result['gate_b_ema'] \\\n","                           and result['gate_b_vol']\n","\n","    # ── GATE C: Momentum ──────────────────────────────────\n","    result['gate_c'] = row['RSI'] > RSI_THRESHOLD\n","\n","    # ── FINAL DECISION ────────────────────────────────────\n","    if result['gate_a'] and result['gate_b'] and result['gate_c']:\n","        result['decision'] = 'EXECUTE'\n","    elif result['gate_b'] and result['gate_c']:\n","        result['decision'] = 'WAIT_GATE_A'  # Need price at zone\n","    elif result['gate_a'] and result['gate_c']:\n","        result['decision'] = 'WAIT_GATE_B'  # Need EMA alignment\n","    elif result['gate_a'] and result['gate_b']:\n","        result['decision'] = 'WAIT_GATE_C'  # Need RSI > 50\n","    else:\n","        result['decision'] = 'IDLE'\n","\n","    return result\n","\n","# Apply engine to all rows\n","print(\"      Evaluating gates for all trading days...\")\n","gate_results = df.apply(\n","    lambda row: evaluate_gates(row, support_zones, resistance_zones),\n","    axis=1\n",")\n","gate_df = pd.DataFrame(gate_results.tolist())\n","df = pd.concat([df, gate_df], axis=1)\n","\n","# ============================================================\n","# MODULE 5 — GENERATE EXECUTION COORDINATES\n","# ============================================================\n","print(\"\\n[5/6] Generating execution coordinates...\")\n","\n","def get_execution_coordinates(price, zone_mid, zone_type,\n","                               support_zones, resistance_zones):\n","    \"\"\"\n","    Calculates Entry, Stop-Loss, and Take-Profit levels.\n","    Risk-Reward must be >= 2:1 for a valid setup.\n","    \"\"\"\n","    entry = price\n","\n","    if zone_type == 'SUPPORT':\n","        # Buying at support: stop below zone, target next resistance\n","        nearest_support = min(\n","            [z['low'] for z in support_zones],\n","            key=lambda x: abs(x - price)\n","        )\n","        stop_loss = round(nearest_support * 0.99, 2)  # 1% below zone\n","\n","        # Find nearest resistance above current price\n","        resistances_above = [\n","            z['mid'] for z in resistance_zones\n","            if z['mid'] > price\n","        ]\n","        if resistances_above:\n","            take_profit = round(min(resistances_above), 2)\n","        else:\n","            take_profit = round(price * 1.05, 2)  # default 5% target\n","\n","    elif zone_type == 'RESISTANCE':\n","        # Shorting at resistance: stop above zone, target next support\n","        nearest_resistance = max(\n","            [z['high'] for z in resistance_zones],\n","            key=lambda x: abs(x - price)\n","        )\n","        stop_loss = round(nearest_resistance * 1.01, 2)\n","\n","        supports_below = [\n","            z['mid'] for z in support_zones\n","            if z['mid'] < price\n","        ]\n","        if supports_below:\n","            take_profit = round(max(supports_below), 2)\n","        else:\n","            take_profit = round(price * 0.95, 2)\n","    else:\n","        return None\n","\n","    risk   = abs(entry - stop_loss)\n","    reward = abs(take_profit - entry)\n","    rr     = round(reward / risk, 2) if risk > 0 else 0\n","\n","    return {\n","        'entry'      : round(entry, 2),\n","        'stop_loss'  : stop_loss,\n","        'take_profit': take_profit,\n","        'risk'       : round(risk, 2),\n","        'reward'     : round(reward, 2),\n","        'rr_ratio'   : rr,\n","        'valid'      : rr >= 2.0  # minimum 2:1 required\n","    }\n","\n","# ============================================================\n","# MODULE 6 — FINAL REPORT\n","# ============================================================\n","print(\"\\n[6/6] Generating engine report...\")\n","\n","# Current state\n","latest = df.iloc[-1]\n","\n","print(f\"\\n{'='*65}\")\n","print(f\"  ENGINE REPORT — {TICKER} — {datetime.now().strftime('%Y-%m-%d')}\")\n","print(f\"{'='*65}\")\n","print(f\"  Current Price : ₹{latest['Close']:.2f}\")\n","print(f\"  EMA-50        : ₹{latest['EMA_50']:.2f}\")\n","print(f\"  EMA-200       : ₹{latest['EMA_200']:.2f}\")\n","print(f\"  RSI (14)      : {latest['RSI']:.2f}\")\n","print(f\"  R_wb          : {latest['R_wb']}\")\n","print(f\"\\n  ── GATE RESULTS ──────────────────────────────\")\n","print(f\"  Gate A (Zone) : {'PASS' if latest['gate_a_zone'] else 'FAIL'}\"\n","      f\"  | Zone type: {latest['zone_type']}\")\n","print(f\"  Gate A (R_wb) : {'PASS' if latest['gate_a_rwb'] else 'FAIL'}\"\n","      f\"  | R_wb = {latest['R_wb']}\")\n","print(f\"  Gate A TOTAL  : {'✓ PASS' if latest['gate_a'] else '✗ FAIL'}\")\n","print(f\"\\n  Gate B (EMA)  : {'PASS' if latest['gate_b_ema'] else 'FAIL'}\"\n","      f\"  | 50 {'>' if latest['gate_b_ema'] else '<'} 200\")\n","print(f\"  Gate B (Vol)  : {'PASS' if latest['gate_b_vol'] else 'FAIL'}\"\n","      f\"  | 1m vol {'>' if latest['gate_b_vol'] else '<'} 1yr vol\")\n","print(f\"  Gate B TOTAL  : {'✓ PASS' if latest['gate_b'] else '✗ FAIL'}\")\n","print(f\"\\n  Gate C (RSI)  : {'✓ PASS' if latest['gate_c'] else '✗ FAIL'}\"\n","      f\"  | RSI = {latest['RSI']:.2f}\")\n","print(f\"\\n{'─'*65}\")\n","print(f\"  FINAL DECISION: {latest['decision']}\")\n","print(f\"{'='*65}\")\n","\n","# Execution coordinates if EXECUTE\n","if latest['decision'] == 'EXECUTE' and latest['zone_mid']:\n","    coords = get_execution_coordinates(\n","        latest['Close'], latest['zone_mid'],\n","        latest['zone_type'],\n","        support_zones, resistance_zones\n","    )\n","    if coords:\n","        print(f\"\\n  ── EXECUTION COORDINATES ─────────────────────\")\n","        print(f\"  Entry        : ₹{coords['entry']}\")\n","        print(f\"  Stop-Loss    : ₹{coords['stop_loss']}\")\n","        print(f\"  Take-Profit  : ₹{coords['take_profit']}\")\n","        print(f\"  Risk         : ₹{coords['risk']}\")\n","        print(f\"  Reward       : ₹{coords['reward']}\")\n","        print(f\"  R:R Ratio    : {coords['rr_ratio']}:1\")\n","        print(f\"  Setup Valid  : {'YES ✓' if coords['valid'] else 'NO ✗ (R:R < 2:1)'}\")\n","\n","# Decision distribution\n","print(f\"\\n  ── HISTORICAL DECISION DISTRIBUTION ──────────\")\n","for state in ['EXECUTE','WAIT_GATE_A','WAIT_GATE_B',\n","              'WAIT_GATE_C','IDLE']:\n","    count = (df['decision'] == state).sum()\n","    pct   = count / len(df) * 100\n","    bar   = '█' * int(pct / 2)\n","    print(f\"  {state:<14}: {count:>4} days \"\n","          f\"({pct:5.1f}%)  {bar}\")\n","\n","# ============================================================\n","# VISUALIZATION\n","# ============================================================\n","fig = plt.figure(figsize=(18, 14))\n","gs  = gridspec.GridSpec(4, 1, height_ratios=[3, 1, 1, 1],\n","                        hspace=0.4)\n","\n","ax1 = fig.add_subplot(gs[0])\n","ax2 = fig.add_subplot(gs[1], sharex=ax1)\n","ax3 = fig.add_subplot(gs[2], sharex=ax1)\n","ax4 = fig.add_subplot(gs[3], sharex=ax1)\n","\n","# Color map for decisions\n","decision_colors = {\n","    'EXECUTE'    : 'green',\n","    'WAIT_GATE_A': 'yellow',\n","    'WAIT_GATE_B': 'orange',\n","    'WAIT_GATE_C': 'skyblue',\n","    'IDLE'       : 'red'\n","}\n","\n","# Shade background by engine decision\n","for i in range(1, len(df)):\n","    color = decision_colors.get(df['decision'].iloc[i], 'gray')\n","    ax1.axvspan(df.index[i-1], df.index[i],\n","                alpha=0.07, color=color)\n","\n","# Price + EMAs\n","ax1.plot(df.index, df['Close'],\n","         color='black', linewidth=0.9, zorder=3)\n","ax1.plot(df.index, df['EMA_50'],\n","         color='steelblue', linewidth=1.8, label='EMA-50')\n","ax1.plot(df.index, df['EMA_200'],\n","         color='darkorange', linewidth=2.2, label='EMA-200')\n","\n","# Support zones\n","for zone in support_zones:\n","    ax1.axhspan(zone['low'], zone['high'],\n","                alpha=0.08, color='green')\n","\n","# Resistance zones\n","for zone in resistance_zones:\n","    ax1.axhspan(zone['low'], zone['high'],\n","                alpha=0.08, color='red')\n","\n","# EXECUTE signals\n","execute_days = df[df['decision'] == 'EXECUTE']\n","ax1.scatter(execute_days.index, execute_days['Close'],\n","            color='gold', marker='*', s=120,\n","            zorder=6, label='EXECUTE signal')\n","\n","ax1.set_title(\n","    f'IPO Decision Engine — {TICKER}  |  '\n","    'Green=EXECUTE  Yellow=WAIT_A  '\n","    'Orange=WAIT_B  Blue=WAIT_C  Red=IDLE',\n","    fontsize=11\n",")\n","ax1.set_ylabel('Price (₹)')\n","ax1.legend(loc='upper left', fontsize=9)\n","\n","# RSI\n","ax2.plot(df.index, df['RSI'], color='purple', linewidth=1.2)\n","ax2.axhline(y=50, color='black', linewidth=1.2, linestyle='-')\n","ax2.axhline(y=70, color='red',   linewidth=0.8, linestyle='--')\n","ax2.axhline(y=30, color='green', linewidth=0.8, linestyle='--')\n","ax2.fill_between(df.index, df['RSI'], 50,\n","                 where=df['RSI'] > 50,\n","                 alpha=0.15, color='green')\n","ax2.fill_between(df.index, df['RSI'], 50,\n","                 where=df['RSI'] < 50,\n","                 alpha=0.15, color='red')\n","ax2.set_ylabel('RSI')\n","ax2.set_ylim(0, 100)\n","ax2.set_title('Gate C — RSI (14) | Black line = 50 threshold', fontsize=10)\n","\n","# R_wb\n","ax3.bar(df.index, df['R_wb'].fillna(0),\n","        color=['red' if r > RWB_THRESHOLD else 'steelblue'\n","               for r in df['R_wb'].fillna(0)],\n","        alpha=0.6, width=1)\n","ax3.axhline(y=RWB_THRESHOLD, color='orange',\n","            linestyle='--', linewidth=1.5)\n","ax3.set_ylabel('R_wb')\n","ax3.set_title(f'Gate A — R_wb Ratio | '\n","              f'Red bars = rejection (>{RWB_THRESHOLD})', fontsize=10)\n","\n","# EMA gap\n","gap = df['EMA_50'] - df['EMA_200']\n","ax4.bar(df.index, gap,\n","        color=['green' if g > 0 else 'red'\n","               for g in gap.fillna(0)],\n","        alpha=0.6, width=1)\n","ax4.axhline(y=0, color='black', linewidth=1.2)\n","ax4.set_ylabel('EMA Gap')\n","ax4.set_title('Gate B — EMA Gap (50-200) | '\n","              'Green = bullish structure', fontsize=10)\n","\n","plt.savefig('stage7_ipo_engine.png', dpi=150, bbox_inches='tight')\n","plt.show()\n","print(\"\\nChart saved as stage7_ipo_engine.png\")\n","print(\"\\nIPO Decision Engine — complete pipeline operational.\")"],"metadata":{"id":"gpWJMUXWitmU","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1780642185795,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":8538,"user":{"displayName":"","userId":""}},"outputId":"3d217e3f-1cfb-46dd-b32f-63f36aea728b","colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":1000}},"execution_count":16,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["=================================================================\n","   IPO DECISION ENGINE — COMPLETE PIPELINE\n","   DecodeLabs Project 1 — Systematic Trading System\n","=================================================================\n","\n","[1/6] Loading market data...\n","      Loaded 498 trading days for RELIANCE.NS\n","\n","[2/6] Calculating indicators...\n","      EMA-50, EMA-200, RSI-14, R_wb, Volume MAs computed\n","\n","[3/6] Mapping support & resistance zones...\n","      Support zones: 6 | Resistance zones: 8\n","\n","[4/6] Running three-gate evaluation...\n","      Evaluating gates for all trading days...\n","\n","[5/6] Generating execution coordinates...\n","\n","[6/6] Generating engine report...\n","\n","=================================================================\n","  ENGINE REPORT — RELIANCE.NS — 2026-06-05\n","=================================================================\n","  Current Price : ₹1297.90\n","  EMA-50        : ₹1358.47\n","  EMA-200       : ₹1399.80\n","  RSI (14)      : 34.79\n","  R_wb          : 0.9242\n","\n","  ── GATE RESULTS ──────────────────────────────\n","  Gate A (Zone) : PASS  | Zone type: SUPPORT\n","  Gate A (R_wb) : FAIL  | R_wb = 0.9242\n","  Gate A TOTAL  : ✗ FAIL\n","\n","  Gate B (EMA)  : FAIL  | 50 < 200\n","  Gate B (Vol)  : PASS  | 1m vol > 1yr vol\n","  Gate B TOTAL  : ✗ FAIL\n","\n","  Gate C (RSI)  : ✗ FAIL  | RSI = 34.79\n","\n","─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n","  FINAL DECISION: IDLE\n","=================================================================\n","\n","  ── HISTORICAL DECISION DISTRIBUTION ──────────\n","  EXECUTE       :    2 days (  0.4%)  \n","  WAIT_GATE_A   :    6 days (  1.2%)  \n","  WAIT_GATE_B   :   55 days ( 11.0%)  █████\n","  WAIT_GATE_C   :    4 days (  0.8%)  \n","  IDLE          :  431 days ( 86.5%)  ███████████████████████████████████████████\n"]},{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<Figure size 1800x1400 with 4 Axes>"],"image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}},{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["\n","Chart saved as stage7_ipo_engine.png\n","\n","IPO Decision Engine — complete pipeline operational.\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["import yfinance as yf\n","import pandas as pd\n","import numpy as np\n","import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n","import matplotlib.gridspec as gridspec\n","from datetime import datetime, time\n","\n","print(\"=\" * 65)\n","print(\"   RISK MANAGEMENT MODULE — DECODELABS PROJECT 1\")\n","print(\"=\" * 65)\n","\n","# ============================================================\n","# CONFIGURATION\n","# ============================================================\n","INITIAL_CAPITAL    = 100_000   # ₹1,00,000 starting capital\n","DAILY_LOSS_LIMIT   = 0.02      # 2% max loss per day\n","RISK_PER_TRADE     = 0.01      # 1% of capital risked per trade\n","MIN_RR_RATIO       = 2.0       # minimum reward:risk ratio\n","\n","# Circuit breaker thresholds (from Slide 15)\n","CB1_THRESHOLD      = 0.50  # Hard stop at 50% of daily limit\n","CB2_CONSECUTIVE    = 2     # Half-size after 2 consecutive losses\n","CB3_THRESHOLD      = 0.70  # Session end at 70% of daily limit\n","CB3_CUTOFF_HOUR    = 13    # 1:00 PM session end time\n","\n","# ============================================================\n","# MODULE 1 — POSITION SIZING\n","# ============================================================\n","\n","def calculate_position_size(capital, entry, stop_loss,\n","                             risk_pct=RISK_PER_TRADE,\n","                             size_multiplier=1.0):\n","    \"\"\"\n","    Calculates how many shares/units to buy based on:\n","    - How much capital we're willing to risk (risk_pct)\n","    - How far the stop-loss is from entry\n","\n","    Formula:\n","    Position Size = (Capital × Risk%) / (Entry - Stop Loss)\n","\n","    Example:\n","    Capital=₹1,00,000, Risk=1%, Entry=₹500, SL=₹485\n","    Risk amount = ₹1,000\n","    Risk per share = ₹15\n","    Position size = ₹1,000 / ₹15 = 66 shares\n","    \"\"\"\n","    risk_amount    = capital * risk_pct * size_multiplier\n","    risk_per_share = abs(entry - stop_loss)\n","\n","    if risk_per_share == 0:\n","        return 0\n","\n","    position_size = int(risk_amount / risk_per_share)\n","    return max(position_size, 0)\n","\n","# Demonstrate position sizing\n","print(\"\\n=== POSITION SIZING DEMONSTRATION ===\")\n","examples = [\n","    (500,  485, \"Reliance support bounce\"),\n","    (1200, 1175, \"TCS EMA-50 touch\"),\n","    (800,  772, \"Infosys resistance retest\"),\n","]\n","\n","for entry, sl, name in examples:\n","    size    = calculate_position_size(\n","        INITIAL_CAPITAL, entry, sl\n","    )\n","    risk_amt = abs(entry - sl) * size\n","    print(f\"\\n  Setup    : {name}\")\n","    print(f\"  Entry    : ₹{entry} | Stop: ₹{sl}\")\n","    print(f\"  Risk/share: ₹{abs(entry-sl)}\")\n","    print(f\"  Shares   : {size}\")\n","    print(f\"  Capital  : ₹{size*entry:,.0f} deployed\")\n","    print(f\"  Max loss : ₹{risk_amt:,.0f} \"\n","          f\"({risk_amt/INITIAL_CAPITAL*100:.1f}% of capital)\")\n","\n","# ============================================================\n","# MODULE 2 — CIRCUIT BREAKER SYSTEM\n","# ============================================================\n","\n","class CircuitBreakerSystem:\n","    \"\"\"\n","    Implements all three mechanical circuit breakers from Slide 15.\n","    Tracks session state and enforces rules automatically.\n","    \"\"\"\n","\n","    def __init__(self, capital, daily_loss_limit_pct):\n","        self.capital            = capital\n","        self.daily_loss_limit   = capital * daily_loss_limit_pct\n","        self.session_pnl        = 0.0\n","        self.consecutive_losses = 0\n","        self.size_multiplier    = 1.0\n","        self.trades_today       = []\n","        self.circuit_breakers   = {\n","            'cb1_hard_stop' : False,  # 15-min stop\n","            'cb2_half_size' : False,  # half position\n","            'cb3_session_end': False  # day ended early\n","        }\n","        self.log = []\n","\n","    def _log(self, message):\n","        timestamp = datetime.now().strftime('%H:%M:%S')\n","        entry = f\"[{timestamp}] {message}\"\n","        self.log.append(entry)\n","        print(f\"  {entry}\")\n","\n","    def check_circuit_breakers(self, current_hour=None):\n","        \"\"\"\n","        Checks all three circuit breakers after each trade.\n","        Returns True if trading is allowed, False if blocked.\n","        \"\"\"\n","        loss_so_far     = abs(min(self.session_pnl, 0))\n","        pct_of_limit    = loss_so_far / self.daily_loss_limit \\\n","                          if self.daily_loss_limit > 0 else 0\n","\n","        # ── CB3: Session End Trigger ──────────────────────\n","        if current_hour and current_hour >= CB3_CUTOFF_HOUR:\n","            if pct_of_limit >= CB3_THRESHOLD:\n","                self.circuit_breakers['cb3_session_end'] = True\n","                self._log(\n","                    f\"⚠ CB3 TRIGGERED: {pct_of_limit*100:.1f}% of \"\n","                    f\"daily limit reached before \"\n","                    f\"{CB3_CUTOFF_HOUR}:00. Session LOCKED.\"\n","                )\n","                return False\n","\n","        # ── CB1: 15-Minute Hard Stop ──────────────────────\n","        if pct_of_limit >= CB1_THRESHOLD \\\n","           and not self.circuit_breakers['cb1_hard_stop']:\n","            self.circuit_breakers['cb1_hard_stop'] = True\n","            self._log(\n","                f\"⚠ CB1 TRIGGERED: Drawdown at \"\n","                f\"{pct_of_limit*100:.1f}% of daily limit. \"\n","                f\"15-minute hard stop activated. Step away.\"\n","            )\n","            return False\n","\n","        # ── CB2: Half-Size Rule ───────────────────────────\n","        if self.consecutive_losses >= CB2_CONSECUTIVE \\\n","           and not self.circuit_breakers['cb2_half_size']:\n","            self.circuit_breakers['cb2_half_size'] = True\n","            self.size_multiplier = 0.5\n","            self._log(\n","                f\"⚠ CB2 TRIGGERED: {self.consecutive_losses} \"\n","                f\"consecutive losses. Position size reduced to 50%.\"\n","            )\n","\n","        return True\n","\n","    def record_trade(self, trade_pnl, current_hour=None):\n","        \"\"\"\n","        Records a completed trade and updates all state.\n","        Returns whether trading is still allowed.\n","        \"\"\"\n","        self.session_pnl += trade_pnl\n","        self.trades_today.append(trade_pnl)\n","\n","        if trade_pnl < 0:\n","            self.consecutive_losses += 1\n","        else:\n","            self.consecutive_losses = 0\n","            # Reset CB2 on a winning trade\n","            if self.circuit_breakers['cb2_half_size']:\n","                self.circuit_breakers['cb2_half_size'] = False\n","                self.size_multiplier = 1.0\n","                self._log(\"CB2 reset: winning trade, \"\n","                          \"position size restored to 100%.\")\n","\n","        result = \"WIN\" if trade_pnl >= 0 else \"LOSS\"\n","        self._log(\n","            f\"Trade {len(self.trades_today)}: \"\n","            f\"{result} ₹{trade_pnl:+,.0f} | \"\n","            f\"Session P&L: ₹{self.session_pnl:+,.0f} | \"\n","            f\"Consecutive losses: {self.consecutive_losses}\"\n","        )\n","\n","        return self.check_circuit_breakers(current_hour)\n","\n","    def get_position_multiplier(self):\n","        return self.size_multiplier\n","\n","    def session_summary(self):\n","        print(f\"\\n  ── SESSION SUMMARY ─────────────────────────\")\n","        print(f\"  Starting capital    : ₹{self.capital:,.0f}\")\n","        print(f\"  Daily loss limit    : ₹{self.daily_loss_limit:,.0f}\")\n","        print(f\"  Session P&L         : ₹{self.session_pnl:+,.0f}\")\n","        print(f\"  Total trades        : {len(self.trades_today)}\")\n","        wins   = sum(1 for t in self.trades_today if t > 0)\n","        losses = sum(1 for t in self.trades_today if t < 0)\n","        print(f\"  Wins / Losses       : {wins} / {losses}\")\n","        if self.trades_today:\n","            win_rate = wins / len(self.trades_today) * 100\n","            print(f\"  Win rate            : {win_rate:.1f}%\")\n","        print(f\"  CB1 (Hard Stop)     : \"\n","              f\"{'TRIGGERED' if self.circuit_breakers['cb1_hard_stop'] else 'OK'}\")\n","        print(f\"  CB2 (Half Size)     : \"\n","              f\"{'TRIGGERED' if self.circuit_breakers['cb2_half_size'] else 'OK'}\")\n","        print(f\"  CB3 (Session End)   : \"\n","              f\"{'TRIGGERED' if self.circuit_breakers['cb3_session_end'] else 'OK'}\")\n","\n","# ============================================================\n","# MODULE 3 — SIMULATE A TRADING SESSION\n","# ============================================================\n","print(\"\\n\\n=== SIMULATED TRADING SESSION ===\")\n","print(\"    (Demonstrating circuit breakers in action)\\n\")\n","\n","cb_system = CircuitBreakerSystem(\n","    capital=INITIAL_CAPITAL,\n","    daily_loss_limit_pct=DAILY_LOSS_LIMIT\n",")\n","\n","# Simulated trades: (pnl, hour, description)\n","simulated_trades = [\n","    ( 1200, 10, \"EXECUTE signal — Reliance support bounce\"),\n","    (-800,  10, \"EXECUTE signal — TCS pullback entry\"),\n","    (-900,  11, \"EXECUTE signal — Infosys zone test\"),\n","    ( 600,  11, \"EXECUTE signal — HDFC EMA touch\"),\n","    (-750,  12, \"EXECUTE signal — Nifty futures long\"),\n","    (-600,  12, \"EXECUTE signal — BankNifty support\"),\n","]\n","\n","print(f\"  Daily loss limit: ₹{INITIAL_CAPITAL * DAILY_LOSS_LIMIT:,.0f}\\n\")\n","\n","for pnl, hour, desc in simulated_trades:\n","    print(f\"\\n  → Attempting: {desc}\")\n","    size_mult = cb_system.get_position_multiplier()\n","    if size_mult < 1.0:\n","        adjusted_pnl = pnl * size_mult\n","        print(f\"    Position size: {size_mult*100:.0f}% \"\n","              f\"(CB2 active) → P&L adjusted to ₹{adjusted_pnl:+,.0f}\")\n","        pnl = adjusted_pnl\n","\n","    can_trade = cb_system.record_trade(pnl, current_hour=hour)\n","\n","    if not can_trade:\n","        print(f\"\\n  ✗ ENGINE LOCKED — no further trades this session\")\n","        break\n","\n","cb_system.session_summary()\n","\n","# ============================================================\n","# MODULE 4 — DRAWDOWN ANALYSIS ON HISTORICAL DATA\n","# ============================================================\n","print(\"\\n\\n=== HISTORICAL DRAWDOWN ANALYSIS ===\")\n","\n","# Simulate an equity curve using the IPO engine signals\n","# (using random walk for demonstration — replace with\n","# actual backtest results from Stage 9)\n","np.random.seed(42)\n","n_trades = 200\n","win_rate = 0.55\n","rr_ratio = 2.0\n","risk_per_trade = INITIAL_CAPITAL * RISK_PER_TRADE\n","\n","equity_curve = [INITIAL_CAPITAL]\n","trade_results = []\n","\n","for i in range(n_trades):\n","    win = np.random.random() < win_rate\n","    if win:\n","        pnl = risk_per_trade * rr_ratio\n","    else:\n","        pnl = -risk_per_trade\n","    equity_curve.append(equity_curve[-1] + pnl)\n","    trade_results.append(pnl)\n","\n","equity = np.array(equity_curve)\n","\n","# Calculate running maximum (peak)\n","running_max = np.maximum.accumulate(equity)\n","\n","# Drawdown at each point\n","drawdowns = (equity - running_max) / running_max * 100\n","\n","# Maximum drawdown\n","max_drawdown     = drawdowns.min()\n","max_dd_idx       = drawdowns.argmin()\n","peak_before_mdd  = running_max[max_dd_idx]\n","\n","# Sharpe ratio (simplified daily)\n","returns    = np.diff(equity) / equity[:-1]\n","sharpe     = (returns.mean() / returns.std()\n","              * np.sqrt(252)) if returns.std() > 0 else 0\n","\n","# Win/loss stats\n","wins       = [t for t in trade_results if t > 0]\n","losses_    = [t for t in trade_results if t < 0]\n","actual_wr  = len(wins) / len(trade_results) * 100\n","avg_win    = np.mean(wins)    if wins    else 0\n","avg_loss   = np.mean(losses_) if losses_ else 0\n","actual_rr  = abs(avg_win / avg_loss) if avg_loss != 0 else 0\n","\n","print(f\"\\n  Simulation: {n_trades} trades | \"\n","      f\"Win rate: {win_rate*100:.0f}% | RR: {rr_ratio}:1\")\n","print(f\"\\n  ── PERFORMANCE METRICS ─────────────────────\")\n","print(f\"  Starting capital    : ₹{INITIAL_CAPITAL:,.0f}\")\n","print(f\"  Final capital       : ₹{equity[-1]:,.0f}\")\n","print(f\"  Total return        : \"\n","      f\"{(equity[-1]/INITIAL_CAPITAL-1)*100:.1f}%\")\n","print(f\"  Actual win rate     : {actual_wr:.1f}%\")\n","print(f\"  Actual R:R ratio    : {actual_rr:.2f}:1\")\n","print(f\"  Sharpe ratio        : {sharpe:.2f}\")\n","print(f\"  Max drawdown        : {max_drawdown:.2f}%\")\n","print(f\"  Peak before MDD     : ₹{peak_before_mdd:,.0f}\")\n","print(f\"  Recovery needed     : \"\n","      f\"{abs(max_drawdown)/(1+max_drawdown/100)*100:.1f}%\")\n","\n","# ============================================================\n","# VISUALIZATION\n","# ============================================================\n","fig = plt.figure(figsize=(16, 12))\n","gs  = gridspec.GridSpec(3, 1, height_ratios=[2, 1, 1],\n","                        hspace=0.4)\n","\n","ax1 = fig.add_subplot(gs[0])\n","ax2 = fig.add_subplot(gs[1], sharex=ax1)\n","ax3 = fig.add_subplot(gs[2])\n","\n","# Equity curve\n","ax1.plot(equity, color='steelblue',\n","         linewidth=1.8, label='Equity Curve')\n","ax1.plot(running_max, color='green',\n","         linewidth=1, linestyle='--',\n","         alpha=0.7, label='Running Peak')\n","ax1.fill_between(range(len(equity)), equity, running_max,\n","                 alpha=0.15, color='red', label='Drawdown area')\n","\n","# Mark maximum drawdown\n","ax1.annotate(\n","    f'Max DD: {max_drawdown:.1f}%',\n","    xy=(max_dd_idx, equity[max_dd_idx]),\n","    xytext=(max_dd_idx + 10, equity[max_dd_idx] * 0.97),\n","    arrowprops=dict(arrowstyle='->', color='red'),\n","    color='red', fontsize=9\n",")\n","\n","ax1.set_title(\n","    f'Equity Curve — {n_trades} Trades | '\n","    f'Win Rate: {actual_wr:.1f}% | '\n","    f'R:R: {actual_rr:.2f}:1 | '\n","    f'Sharpe: {sharpe:.2f}',\n","    fontsize=11\n",")\n","ax1.set_ylabel('Portfolio Value (₹)')\n","ax1.legend(loc='upper left')\n","\n","# Drawdown chart\n","ax2.fill_between(range(len(drawdowns)), drawdowns, 0,\n","                 alpha=0.6, color='red')\n","ax2.axhline(y=max_drawdown, color='darkred',\n","            linestyle='--', linewidth=1.2,\n","            label=f'Max DD: {max_drawdown:.1f}%')\n","ax2.axhline(y=-DAILY_LOSS_LIMIT * 100 * CB1_THRESHOLD,\n","            color='orange', linestyle='--',\n","            label=f'CB1 level ({CB1_THRESHOLD*100:.0f}% of limit)')\n","ax2.set_ylabel('Drawdown (%)')\n","ax2.set_title('Drawdown Over Time', fontsize=10)\n","ax2.legend(fontsize=8)\n","\n","# Trade distribution\n","colors_ = ['green' if t > 0 else 'red' for t in trade_results]\n","ax3.bar(range(len(trade_results)), trade_results,\n","        color=colors_, alpha=0.6, width=1)\n","ax3.axhline(y=0, color='black', linewidth=1)\n","ax3.axhline(y=risk_per_trade * rr_ratio,\n","            color='green', linestyle='--',\n","            linewidth=1, label=f'Target: ₹{risk_per_trade*rr_ratio:,.0f}')\n","ax3.axhline(y=-risk_per_trade,\n","            color='red', linestyle='--',\n","            linewidth=1, label=f'Stop: -₹{risk_per_trade:,.0f}')\n","ax3.set_ylabel('Trade P&L (₹)')\n","ax3.set_title('Individual Trade Results', fontsize=10)\n","ax3.legend(fontsize=8)\n","\n","plt.savefig('stage8_risk_management.png', dpi=150,\n","            bbox_inches='tight')\n","plt.show()\n","print(\"\\nChart saved as stage8_risk_management.png\")"],"metadata":{"id":"XkBqDgNBjeX1","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1780642409403,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":6052,"user":{"displayName":"","userId":""}},"outputId":"61be25c9-031d-40a4-ba27-c625a29633c7","colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":1000}},"execution_count":17,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["=================================================================\n","   RISK MANAGEMENT MODULE — DECODELABS PROJECT 1\n","=================================================================\n","\n","=== POSITION SIZING DEMONSTRATION ===\n","\n","  Setup    : Reliance support bounce\n","  Entry    : ₹500 | Stop: ₹485\n","  Risk/share: ₹15\n","  Shares   : 66\n","  Capital  : ₹33,000 deployed\n","  Max loss : ₹990 (1.0% of capital)\n","\n","  Setup    : TCS EMA-50 touch\n","  Entry    : ₹1200 | Stop: ₹1175\n","  Risk/share: ₹25\n","  Shares   : 40\n","  Capital  : ₹48,000 deployed\n","  Max loss : ₹1,000 (1.0% of capital)\n","\n","  Setup    : Infosys resistance retest\n","  Entry    : ₹800 | Stop: ₹772\n","  Risk/share: ₹28\n","  Shares   : 35\n","  Capital  : ₹28,000 deployed\n","  Max loss : ₹980 (1.0% of capital)\n","\n","\n","=== SIMULATED TRADING SESSION ===\n","    (Demonstrating circuit breakers in action)\n","\n","  Daily loss limit: ₹2,000\n","\n","\n","  → Attempting: EXECUTE signal — Reliance support bounce\n","  [06:53:22] Trade 1: WIN ₹+1,200 | Session P&L: ₹+1,200 | Consecutive losses: 0\n","\n","  → Attempting: EXECUTE signal — TCS pullback entry\n","  [06:53:22] Trade 2: LOSS ₹-800 | Session P&L: ₹+400 | Consecutive losses: 1\n","\n","  → Attempting: EXECUTE signal — Infosys zone test\n","  [06:53:22] Trade 3: LOSS ₹-900 | Session P&L: ₹-500 | Consecutive losses: 2\n","  [06:53:22] ⚠ CB2 TRIGGERED: 2 consecutive losses. Position size reduced to 50%.\n","\n","  → Attempting: EXECUTE signal — HDFC EMA touch\n","    Position size: 50% (CB2 active) → P&L adjusted to ₹+300\n","  [06:53:22] CB2 reset: winning trade, position size restored to 100%.\n","  [06:53:22] Trade 4: WIN ₹+300 | Session P&L: ₹-200 | Consecutive losses: 0\n","\n","  → Attempting: EXECUTE signal — Nifty futures long\n","  [06:53:22] Trade 5: LOSS ₹-750 | Session P&L: ₹-950 | Consecutive losses: 1\n","\n","  → Attempting: EXECUTE signal — BankNifty support\n","  [06:53:22] Trade 6: LOSS ₹-600 | Session P&L: ₹-1,550 | Consecutive losses: 2\n","  [06:53:22] ⚠ CB1 TRIGGERED: Drawdown at 77.5% of daily limit. 15-minute hard stop activated. Step away.\n","\n","  ✗ ENGINE LOCKED — no further trades this session\n","\n","  ── SESSION SUMMARY ─────────────────────────\n","  Starting capital    : ₹100,000\n","  Daily loss limit    : ₹2,000\n","  Session P&L         : ₹-1,550\n","  Total trades        : 6\n","  Wins / Losses       : 2 / 4\n","  Win rate            : 33.3%\n","  CB1 (Hard Stop)     : TRIGGERED\n","  CB2 (Half Size)     : OK\n","  CB3 (Session End)   : OK\n","\n","\n","=== HISTORICAL DRAWDOWN ANALYSIS ===\n","\n","  Simulation: 200 trades | Win rate: 55% | RR: 2.0:1\n","\n","  ── PERFORMANCE METRICS ─────────────────────\n","  Starting capital    : ₹100,000\n","  Final capital       : ₹248,000\n","  Total return        : 148.0%\n","  Actual win rate     : 58.0%\n","  Actual R:R ratio    : 2.00:1\n","  Sharpe ratio        : 7.77\n","  Max drawdown        : -4.11%\n","  Peak before MDD     : ₹146,000\n","  Recovery needed     : 428.6%\n"]},{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<Figure size 1600x1200 with 3 Axes>"],"image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}},{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["\n","Chart saved as stage8_risk_management.png\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["import yfinance as yf\n","import pandas as pd\n","import numpy as np\n","import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n","import matplotlib.gridspec as gridspec\n","from datetime import datetime\n","\n","print(\"=\" * 65)\n","print(\"   STAGE 9 — BACKTESTING ENGINE\")\n","print(\"   DecodeLabs Project 1 — Complete Pipeline Validation\")\n","print(\"=\" * 65)\n","\n","# ============================================================\n","# CONFIGURATION\n","# ============================================================\n","TICKER             = \"RELIANCE.NS\"\n","PERIOD             = \"5y\"          # 5 years of data\n","INTERVAL           = \"1d\"\n","\n","# Strategy parameters (from all previous stages)\n","RWB_THRESHOLD      = 2.0\n","ZONE_TOLERANCE     = 0.015\n","ZONE_PROXIMITY     = 0.02\n","SWING_LOOKBACK     = 5\n","RSI_THRESHOLD      = 50\n","VOL_SHORT          = 21\n","VOL_LONG           = 252\n","\n","# Risk management parameters (from Stage 8)\n","INITIAL_CAPITAL    = 100_000\n","RISK_PER_TRADE     = 0.01       # 1% per trade\n","MIN_RR             = 2.0\n","COMMISSION_PCT     = 0.0005     # 0.05% per side (realistic Indian broker)\n","SLIPPAGE_PCT       = 0.001      # 0.10% slippage on entry\n","\n","# Out-of-sample split\n","OOS_SPLIT          = 0.70       # 70% in-sample, 30% out-of-sample\n","\n","# ============================================================\n","# MODULE 1 — DATA LOADING\n","# ============================================================\n","print(\"\\n[1/7] Loading 5 years of market data...\")\n","ticker_obj = yf.Ticker(TICKER)\n","df = ticker_obj.history(period=PERIOD, interval=INTERVAL)\n","df = df[['Open','High','Low','Close','Volume']].copy()\n","df.reset_index(inplace=True)\n","prices = df['Close'].tolist()\n","\n","split_idx   = int(len(df) * OOS_SPLIT)\n","print(f\"      Total rows     : {len(df)} trading days\")\n","print(f\"      In-sample      : rows 0–{split_idx} \"\n","      f\"({df.iloc[0]['Date'].date()} to \"\n","      f\"{df.iloc[split_idx]['Date'].date()})\")\n","print(f\"      Out-of-sample  : rows {split_idx}–{len(df)-1} \"\n","      f\"({df.iloc[split_idx]['Date'].date()} to \"\n","      f\"{df.iloc[-1]['Date'].date()})\")\n","\n","# ============================================================\n","# MODULE 2 — INDICATOR CALCULATIONS (all stages reused)\n","# ============================================================\n","print(\"\\n[2/7] Computing all indicators...\")\n","\n","def calculate_ema(prices, period):\n","    if len(prices) < period:\n","        return [None] * len(prices)\n","    alpha = 2 / (period + 1)\n","    first_sma = sum(prices[:period]) / period\n","    ema_values = [None] * (period - 1)\n","    ema_values.append(first_sma)\n","    for i in range(period, len(prices)):\n","        ema_values.append(alpha * prices[i] +\n","                          (1 - alpha) * ema_values[-1])\n","    return ema_values\n","\n","def calculate_rsi(prices, period=14):\n","    rsi_values = [None] * len(prices)\n","    if len(prices) < period + 1:\n","        return rsi_values\n","    changes  = [prices[i] - prices[i-1] for i in range(1, len(prices))]\n","    gains    = [max(c, 0)       for c in changes]\n","    losses   = [abs(min(c, 0))  for c in changes]\n","    avg_gain = sum(gains[:period])  / period\n","    avg_loss = sum(losses[:period]) / period\n","    def rsi_from_rs(ag, al):\n","        return 100.0 if al == 0 else round(100-(100/(1+ag/al)), 4)\n","    rsi_values[period] = rsi_from_rs(avg_gain, avg_loss)\n","    for i in range(period, len(changes)):\n","        avg_gain = (avg_gain*(period-1) + gains[i])  / period\n","        avg_loss = (avg_loss*(period-1) + losses[i]) / period\n","        rsi_values[i+1] = rsi_from_rs(avg_gain, avg_loss)\n","    return rsi_values\n","\n","def calculate_rwb(row):\n","    upper = row['High'] - max(row['Open'], row['Close'])\n","    lower = min(row['Open'], row['Close']) - row['Low']\n","    body  = abs(row['Open'] - row['Close'])\n","    return round((upper + lower) / body, 4) if body != 0 else None\n","\n","df['EMA_50']  = calculate_ema(prices, 50)\n","df['EMA_200'] = calculate_ema(prices, 200)\n","df['RSI']     = calculate_rsi(prices, 14)\n","df['R_wb']    = df.apply(calculate_rwb, axis=1)\n","df['vol_1m']  = df['Volume'].rolling(VOL_SHORT).mean()\n","df['vol_1yr'] = df['Volume'].rolling(VOL_LONG).mean()\n","print(\"      All indicators computed.\")\n","\n","# ============================================================\n","# MODULE 3 — SUPPORT & RESISTANCE ZONES\n","# ============================================================\n","print(\"\\n[3/7] Mapping structural zones on in-sample data only...\")\n","\n","# CRITICAL: zones are built ONLY on in-sample data\n","# Using out-of-sample data to build zones = look-ahead bias\n","df_is = df.iloc[:split_idx].copy()\n","\n","def find_swing_points(df, lookback=5):\n","    sh, sl = [], []\n","    for i in range(lookback, len(df)-lookback):\n","        if df['High'].iloc[i] == df['High'].iloc[i-lookback:i+lookback+1].max():\n","            sh.append(i)\n","        if df['Low'].iloc[i]  == df['Low'].iloc[i-lookback:i+lookback+1].min():\n","            sl.append(i)\n","    return sh, sl\n","\n","def cluster_zones(indices, prices, tol=0.015):\n","    levels = sorted([prices[i] for i in indices])\n","    zones, used = [], [False]*len(levels)\n","    for i in range(len(levels)):\n","        if used[i]: continue\n","        cluster = [levels[i]]; used[i] = True\n","        for j in range(i+1, len(levels)):\n","            if not used[j] and \\\n","               abs(levels[j]-np.mean(cluster))/np.mean(cluster) < tol:\n","                cluster.append(levels[j]); used[j] = True\n","        if len(cluster) >= 2:\n","            zones.append({\n","                'low': min(cluster), 'high': max(cluster),\n","                'mid': np.mean(cluster), 'strength': len(cluster)\n","            })\n","    return zones\n","\n","sh_idx, sl_idx = find_swing_points(df_is, SWING_LOOKBACK)\n","resistance_zones = cluster_zones(sh_idx, df_is['High'].values)\n","support_zones    = cluster_zones(sl_idx, df_is['Low'].values)\n","\n","print(f\"      Support zones: {len(support_zones)} | \"\n","      f\"Resistance zones: {len(resistance_zones)}\")\n","\n","# ============================================================\n","# MODULE 4 — SIGNAL GENERATION\n","# ============================================================\n","print(\"\\n[4/7] Running IPO engine to generate signals...\")\n","\n","def generate_signal(row, s_zones, r_zones):\n","    \"\"\"Compact version of the full 3-gate engine from Stage 7.\"\"\"\n","    if any(pd.isna([row['EMA_50'], row['EMA_200'],\n","                    row['RSI'], row['R_wb']])):\n","        return 'NO_DATA', None, None\n","\n","    price = row['Close']\n","\n","    # Gate A — zone + rejection\n","    at_zone, zone_type, zone_mid = False, None, None\n","    for z in s_zones:\n","        if abs(price - z['mid']) / price < ZONE_PROXIMITY:\n","            at_zone, zone_type, zone_mid = True, 'SUPPORT', z['mid']\n","            break\n","    if not at_zone:\n","        for z in r_zones:\n","            if abs(price - z['mid']) / price < ZONE_PROXIMITY:\n","                at_zone, zone_type, zone_mid = True, 'RESISTANCE', z['mid']\n","                break\n","\n","    gate_a = at_zone and (row['R_wb'] is not None\n","                          and row['R_wb'] > RWB_THRESHOLD)\n","\n","    # Gate B — EMA + volume\n","    gate_b = (row['EMA_50'] > row['EMA_200'] and\n","              not pd.isna(row['vol_1m']) and\n","              not pd.isna(row['vol_1yr']) and\n","              row['vol_1m'] > row['vol_1yr'])\n","\n","    # Gate C — RSI\n","    gate_c = row['RSI'] > RSI_THRESHOLD\n","\n","    if gate_a and gate_b and gate_c:\n","        return 'EXECUTE', zone_type, zone_mid\n","    return 'IDLE', None, None\n","\n","signals = df.apply(\n","    lambda row: generate_signal(row, support_zones, resistance_zones),\n","    axis=1\n",")\n","df['signal']    = [s[0] for s in signals]\n","df['zone_type'] = [s[1] for s in signals]\n","df['zone_mid']  = [s[2] for s in signals]\n","\n","execute_count = (df['signal'] == 'EXECUTE').sum()\n","print(f\"      EXECUTE signals generated: {execute_count} \"\n","      f\"({execute_count/len(df)*100:.1f}% of days)\")\n","\n","# ============================================================\n","# MODULE 5 — TRADE SIMULATION (THE ACTUAL BACKTEST)\n","# ============================================================\n","print(\"\\n[5/7] Simulating trades with realistic costs...\")\n","\n","trades   = []\n","capital  = INITIAL_CAPITAL\n","in_trade = False\n","entry_price = stop_loss = take_profit = 0\n","entry_date = position_size = 0\n","\n","def get_targets(price, zone_type, s_zones, r_zones):\n","    \"\"\"Get stop-loss and take-profit based on nearest zones.\"\"\"\n","    if zone_type == 'SUPPORT':\n","        sl = price * (1 - 0.02)    # 2% below entry\n","        resistances = [z['mid'] for z in r_zones if z['mid'] > price]\n","        tp = min(resistances) if resistances else price * 1.05\n","    else:\n","        sl = price * (1 + 0.02)\n","        supports = [z['mid'] for z in s_zones if z['mid'] < price]\n","        tp = max(supports) if supports else price * 0.95\n","    return round(sl, 2), round(tp, 2)\n","\n","equity_curve = [INITIAL_CAPITAL]\n","\n","for i in range(1, len(df)):\n","    row   = df.iloc[i]\n","    prev  = df.iloc[i-1]\n","\n","    # ── Check open trade for exit ──────────────────────────\n","    if in_trade:\n","        exit_price = None\n","        exit_reason = None\n","\n","        # Stop-loss hit (use Low of the day)\n","        if prev['zone_type'] == 'SUPPORT' and row['Low'] <= stop_loss:\n","            exit_price  = stop_loss\n","            exit_reason = 'STOP_LOSS'\n","        # Take-profit hit (use High of the day)\n","        elif prev['zone_type'] == 'SUPPORT' and row['High'] >= take_profit:\n","            exit_price  = take_profit\n","            exit_reason = 'TAKE_PROFIT'\n","\n","        if exit_price:\n","            # Apply commission on exit\n","            commission  = exit_price * position_size * COMMISSION_PCT\n","            gross_pnl   = (exit_price - entry_price) * position_size\n","            net_pnl     = gross_pnl - commission * 2  # entry + exit\n","\n","            capital += net_pnl\n","            equity_curve.append(capital)\n","\n","            sample_type = 'IN_SAMPLE' if i < split_idx else 'OUT_OF_SAMPLE'\n","\n","            trades.append({\n","                'entry_date'  : entry_date,\n","                'exit_date'   : row['Date'],\n","                'entry_price' : entry_price,\n","                'exit_price'  : exit_price,\n","                'stop_loss'   : stop_loss,\n","                'take_profit' : take_profit,\n","                'position'    : position_size,\n","                'gross_pnl'   : round(gross_pnl, 2),\n","                'commission'  : round(commission * 2, 2),\n","                'net_pnl'     : round(net_pnl, 2),\n","                'result'      : exit_reason,\n","                'capital_after': round(capital, 2),\n","                'sample'      : sample_type\n","            })\n","            in_trade = False\n","        else:\n","            equity_curve.append(capital)\n","\n","    # ── Check for new entry signal ─────────────────────────\n","    elif row['signal'] == 'EXECUTE' and not in_trade:\n","        raw_entry   = row['Close']\n","        # Apply slippage — you never get the exact close price\n","        entry_price = round(raw_entry * (1 + SLIPPAGE_PCT), 2)\n","        zone_type_  = row['zone_type']\n","\n","        sl, tp = get_targets(entry_price, zone_type_,\n","                             support_zones, resistance_zones)\n","\n","        rr = abs(tp - entry_price) / abs(entry_price - sl)\n","        if rr < MIN_RR:\n","            equity_curve.append(capital)\n","            continue  # Skip trades with insufficient R:R\n","\n","        stop_loss   = sl\n","        take_profit = tp\n","\n","        # Position sizing: risk exactly 1% of current capital\n","        risk_amount   = capital * RISK_PER_TRADE\n","        risk_per_share = abs(entry_price - stop_loss)\n","        position_size = int(risk_amount / risk_per_share) \\\n","                        if risk_per_share > 0 else 0\n","\n","        if position_size > 0:\n","            # Entry commission\n","            commission = entry_price * position_size * COMMISSION_PCT\n","            capital   -= commission\n","            entry_date = row['Date']\n","            in_trade   = True\n","            equity_curve.append(capital)\n","        else:\n","            equity_curve.append(capital)\n","    else:\n","        equity_curve.append(capital)\n","\n","# ============================================================\n","# MODULE 6 — PERFORMANCE ANALYTICS\n","# ============================================================\n","print(\"\\n[6/7] Computing performance metrics...\")\n","\n","trades_df = pd.DataFrame(trades)\n","\n","def performance_report(trades_subset, label, starting_cap):\n","    if trades_subset.empty:\n","        print(f\"\\n  {label}: No trades found.\")\n","        return {}\n","\n","    wins    = trades_subset[trades_subset['net_pnl'] > 0]\n","    losses  = trades_subset[trades_subset['net_pnl'] <= 0]\n","    n       = len(trades_subset)\n","    wr      = len(wins) / n * 100\n","    avg_w   = wins['net_pnl'].mean()   if len(wins)   > 0 else 0\n","    avg_l   = losses['net_pnl'].mean() if len(losses) > 0 else 0\n","    rr      = abs(avg_w / avg_l)       if avg_l != 0   else 0\n","    total   = trades_subset['net_pnl'].sum()\n","    ret_pct = total / starting_cap * 100\n","\n","    # Max drawdown on this subset\n","    caps = [starting_cap] + trades_subset['capital_after'].tolist()\n","    caps_arr = np.array(caps)\n","    peak = np.maximum.accumulate(caps_arr)\n","    dd   = (caps_arr - peak) / peak * 100\n","    mdd  = dd.min()\n","\n","    # Profit factor\n","    gross_profit = wins['net_pnl'].sum()   if len(wins)   > 0 else 0\n","    gross_loss   = abs(losses['net_pnl'].sum()) if len(losses) > 0 else 1\n","    pf           = gross_profit / gross_loss\n","\n","    print(f\"\\n  {'─'*55}\")\n","    print(f\"  {label}\")\n","    print(f\"  {'─'*55}\")\n","    print(f\"  Total trades      : {n}\")\n","    print(f\"  Win rate          : {wr:.1f}%\")\n","    print(f\"  Avg win           : ₹{avg_w:,.0f}\")\n","    print(f\"  Avg loss          : ₹{avg_l:,.0f}\")\n","    print(f\"  R:R achieved      : {rr:.2f}:1\")\n","    print(f\"  Profit factor     : {pf:.2f}\")\n","    print(f\"  Total net P&L     : ₹{total:,.0f}\")\n","    print(f\"  Return            : {ret_pct:.1f}%\")\n","    print(f\"  Max drawdown      : {mdd:.2f}%\")\n","    print(f\"  Commissions paid  : \"\n","          f\"₹{trades_subset['commission'].sum():,.0f}\")\n","\n","    return {'n': n, 'win_rate': wr, 'rr': rr,\n","            'pf': pf, 'ret_pct': ret_pct, 'mdd': mdd}\n","\n","# Split results by in-sample vs out-of-sample\n","if not trades_df.empty:\n","    is_trades  = trades_df[trades_df['sample'] == 'IN_SAMPLE']\n","    oos_trades = trades_df[trades_df['sample'] == 'OUT_OF_SAMPLE']\n","\n","    is_cap  = INITIAL_CAPITAL\n","    oos_cap = is_trades['capital_after'].iloc[-1] \\\n","              if not is_trades.empty else INITIAL_CAPITAL\n","\n","    print(\"\\n\" + \"=\"*65)\n","    is_metrics  = performance_report(is_trades,\n","                  \"IN-SAMPLE RESULTS  (Strategy Development)\",\n","                  is_cap)\n","    oos_metrics = performance_report(oos_trades,\n","                  \"OUT-OF-SAMPLE RESULTS (Real-World Validation)\",\n","                  oos_cap)\n","\n","    # Consistency check\n","    print(f\"\\n  {'─'*55}\")\n","    print(f\"  CONSISTENCY CHECK (In-Sample vs Out-of-Sample)\")\n","    print(f\"  {'─'*55}\")\n","    if is_metrics and oos_metrics:\n","        wr_diff  = abs(is_metrics['win_rate'] - oos_metrics['win_rate'])\n","        rr_diff  = abs(is_metrics['rr']       - oos_metrics['rr'])\n","        print(f\"  Win rate diff : {wr_diff:.1f}%  \"\n","              f\"{'✓ CONSISTENT' if wr_diff < 10 else '⚠ INCONSISTENT — possible overfit'}\")\n","        print(f\"  R:R diff      : {rr_diff:.2f}  \"\n","              f\"{'✓ CONSISTENT' if rr_diff < 0.5 else '⚠ INCONSISTENT — possible overfit'}\")\n","\n","# Full equity curve\n","equity_arr = np.array(equity_curve[:len(df)+1])\n","peak_arr   = np.maximum.accumulate(equity_arr)\n","dd_arr     = (equity_arr - peak_arr) / peak_arr * 100\n","\n","print(f\"\\n  FULL BACKTEST SUMMARY ({TICKER}, 5 years)\")\n","print(f\"  Starting capital  : ₹{INITIAL_CAPITAL:,.0f}\")\n","if equity_arr.size > 0:\n","    print(f\"  Final capital     : ₹{equity_arr[-1]:,.0f}\")\n","    total_ret = (equity_arr[-1]/INITIAL_CAPITAL - 1)*100\n","    print(f\"  Total return      : {total_ret:.1f}%\")\n","    print(f\"  Max drawdown      : {dd_arr.min():.2f}%\")\n","    print(f\"  Total trades      : {len(trades_df)}\")\n","\n","# ============================================================\n","# MODULE 7 — VISUALIZATION\n","# ============================================================\n","print(\"\\n[7/7] Generating backtest report charts...\")\n","\n","fig = plt.figure(figsize=(18, 16))\n","gs  = gridspec.GridSpec(4, 2, hspace=0.45, wspace=0.35)\n","\n","ax_equity   = fig.add_subplot(gs[0, :])   # full width — equity\n","ax_dd       = fig.add_subplot(gs[1, :])   # full width — drawdown\n","ax_dist     = fig.add_subplot(gs[2, 0])   # trade distribution\n","ax_monthly  = fig.add_subplot(gs[2, 1])   # monthly returns\n","ax_rr       = fig.add_subplot(gs[3, 0])   # RR scatter\n","ax_cumwin   = fig.add_subplot(gs[3, 1])   # cumulative win rate\n","\n","# 1. Equity curve\n","ax_equity.plot(range(len(equity_arr)), equity_arr,\n","               color='steelblue', linewidth=1.8, label='Portfolio Value')\n","ax_equity.plot(range(len(peak_arr)), peak_arr,\n","               color='green', linewidth=1, linestyle='--',\n","               alpha=0.6, label='Running Peak')\n","ax_equity.fill_between(range(len(equity_arr)),\n","                        equity_arr, peak_arr,\n","                        alpha=0.12, color='red')\n","\n","# Mark in-sample / out-of-sample boundary\n","ax_equity.axvline(x=split_idx, color='orange',\n","                  linestyle='--', linewidth=2,\n","                  label='In-Sample | Out-of-Sample split')\n","\n","ax_equity.set_title(\n","    f'Equity Curve — {TICKER} — 5-Year Backtest  |  '\n","    f'Orange line = in/out-of-sample split',\n","    fontsize=12\n",")\n","ax_equity.set_ylabel('Portfolio Value (₹)')\n","ax_equity.legend(loc='upper left', fontsize=9)\n","\n","# 2. Drawdown\n","ax_dd.fill_between(range(len(dd_arr)), dd_arr, 0,\n","                   alpha=0.6, color='red')\n","ax_dd.axhline(y=dd_arr.min(), color='darkred',\n","              linestyle='--', linewidth=1.2,\n","              label=f'Max DD: {dd_arr.min():.1f}%')\n","ax_dd.axhline(y=-10, color='orange', linestyle=':', linewidth=1,\n","              label='-10% warning level')\n","ax_dd.set_ylabel('Drawdown (%)')\n","ax_dd.set_title('Portfolio Drawdown Over Time', fontsize=11)\n","ax_dd.legend(fontsize=9)\n","\n","# 3. Trade P&L distribution\n","if not trades_df.empty:\n","    colors_ = ['green' if p > 0 else 'red'\n","               for p in trades_df['net_pnl']]\n","    ax_dist.bar(range(len(trades_df)), trades_df['net_pnl'],\n","                color=colors_, alpha=0.7, width=0.8)\n","    ax_dist.axhline(y=0, color='black', linewidth=1)\n","    ax_dist.set_title('Individual Trade P&L', fontsize=11)\n","    ax_dist.set_xlabel('Trade #')\n","    ax_dist.set_ylabel('Net P&L (₹)')\n","\n","    # 4. Monthly returns heatmap (simplified bar chart)\n","    trades_df['exit_month'] = pd.to_datetime(\n","        trades_df['exit_date']\n","    ).dt.to_period('M')\n","    monthly = trades_df.groupby('exit_month')['net_pnl'].sum()\n","    monthly_colors = ['green' if v > 0 else 'red' for v in monthly]\n","    ax_monthly.bar(range(len(monthly)), monthly.values,\n","                   color=monthly_colors, alpha=0.7)\n","    ax_monthly.axhline(y=0, color='black', linewidth=1)\n","    ax_monthly.set_title('Monthly P&L', fontsize=11)\n","    ax_monthly.set_ylabel('P&L (₹)')\n","    ax_monthly.set_xticks(range(0, len(monthly), 3))\n","    ax_monthly.set_xticklabels(\n","        [str(m) for m in monthly.index[::3]],\n","        rotation=45, fontsize=7\n","    )\n","\n","    # 5. Risk:Reward scatter\n","    trades_df['actual_rr'] = trades_df.apply(\n","        lambda r: abs(r['exit_price']-r['entry_price']) /\n","                  abs(r['entry_price']-r['stop_loss'])\n","                  if abs(r['entry_price']-r['stop_loss']) > 0 else 0,\n","        axis=1\n","    )\n","    win_mask  = trades_df['net_pnl'] > 0\n","    loss_mask = ~win_mask\n","    ax_rr.scatter(trades_df[win_mask].index,\n","                  trades_df[win_mask]['actual_rr'],\n","                  color='green', alpha=0.6, s=40, label='Wins')\n","    ax_rr.scatter(trades_df[loss_mask].index,\n","                  trades_df[loss_mask]['actual_rr'],\n","                  color='red',   alpha=0.6, s=40, label='Losses')\n","    ax_rr.axhline(y=MIN_RR, color='orange',\n","                  linestyle='--', linewidth=1.5,\n","                  label=f'Min R:R = {MIN_RR}')\n","    ax_rr.set_title('Actual R:R Per Trade', fontsize=11)\n","    ax_rr.set_ylabel('R:R Ratio Achieved')\n","    ax_rr.legend(fontsize=8)\n","\n","    # 6. Cumulative win rate\n","    trades_df['cumulative_wr'] = (\n","        (trades_df['net_pnl'] > 0).cumsum() /\n","        (trades_df.index + 1) * 100\n","    )\n","    ax_cumwin.plot(range(len(trades_df)),\n","                   trades_df['cumulative_wr'],\n","                   color='steelblue', linewidth=1.5)\n","    ax_cumwin.axhline(y=50, color='black',\n","                      linestyle='--', linewidth=1,\n","                      label='50% breakeven line')\n","    ax_cumwin.set_title('Cumulative Win Rate Over Time', fontsize=11)\n","    ax_cumwin.set_ylabel('Win Rate (%)')\n","    ax_cumwin.set_ylim(0, 100)\n","    ax_cumwin.legend(fontsize=9)\n","\n","plt.suptitle(\n","    f'IPO Decision Engine — Complete 5-Year Backtest Report\\n'\n","    f'{TICKER}  |  DecodeLabs Project 1',\n","    fontsize=13, fontweight='bold', y=1.01\n",")\n","plt.savefig('stage9_backtest_report.png', dpi=150,\n","            bbox_inches='tight')\n","plt.show()\n","print(\"\\nBacktest report saved as stage9_backtest_report.png\")\n","print(\"\\n✓ STAGE 9 COMPLETE — Full pipeline backtested and validated.\")"],"metadata":{"id":"YfL-a_Mfj9ci","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1780642601948,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":12109,"user":{"displayName":"","userId":""}},"outputId":"5dfe58bd-3831-4802-ee26-128ea3fc87d0","colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":1000}},"execution_count":18,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["=================================================================\n","   STAGE 9 — BACKTESTING ENGINE\n","   DecodeLabs Project 1 — Complete Pipeline Validation\n","=================================================================\n","\n","[1/7] Loading 5 years of market data...\n","      Total rows     : 1238 trading days\n","      In-sample      : rows 0–866 (2021-06-07 to 2024-12-06)\n","      Out-of-sample  : rows 866–1237 (2024-12-06 to 2026-06-05)\n","\n","[2/7] Computing all indicators...\n","      All indicators computed.\n","\n","[3/7] Mapping structural zones on in-sample data only...\n","      Support zones: 11 | Resistance zones: 11\n","\n","[4/7] Running IPO engine to generate signals...\n","      EXECUTE signals generated: 36 (2.9% of days)\n","\n","[5/7] Simulating trades with realistic costs...\n","\n","[6/7] Computing performance metrics...\n","\n","=================================================================\n","\n","  ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n","  IN-SAMPLE RESULTS  (Strategy Development)\n","  ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n","  Total trades      : 2\n","  Win rate          : 50.0%\n","  Avg win           : ₹925\n","  Avg loss          : ₹-2,296\n","  R:R achieved      : 0.40:1\n","  Profit factor     : 0.40\n","  Total net P&L     : ₹-1,370\n","  Return            : -1.4%\n","  Max drawdown      : -2.30%\n","  Commissions paid  : ₹97\n","\n","  ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n","  OUT-OF-SAMPLE RESULTS (Real-World Validation)\n","  ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n","  Total trades      : 2\n","  Win rate          : 50.0%\n","  Avg win           : ₹908\n","  Avg loss          : ₹-1,042\n","  R:R achieved      : 0.87:1\n","  Profit factor     : 0.87\n","  Total net P&L     : ₹-134\n","  Return            : -0.1%\n","  Max drawdown      : -1.07%\n","  Commissions paid  : ₹97\n","\n","  ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n","  CONSISTENCY CHECK (In-Sample vs Out-of-Sample)\n","  ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n","  Win rate diff : 0.0%  ✓ CONSISTENT\n","  R:R diff      : 0.47  ✓ CONSISTENT\n","\n","  FULL BACKTEST SUMMARY (RELIANCE.NS, 5 years)\n","  Starting capital  : ₹100,000\n","  Final capital     : ₹98,374\n","  Total return      : -1.6%\n","  Max drawdown      : -2.50%\n","  Total trades      : 4\n","\n","[7/7] Generating backtest report charts...\n"]},{"output_type":"stream","name":"stderr","text":["/tmp/ipykernel_1450/2883536702.py:470: UserWarning: Converting to PeriodArray/Index representation will drop timezone information.\n","  ).dt.to_period('M')\n"]},{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<Figure size 1800x1600 with 6 Axes>"],"image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}},{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["\n","Backtest report saved as stage9_backtest_report.png\n","\n","✓ STAGE 9 COMPLETE — Full pipeline backtested and validated.\n"]}]}],"metadata":{"colab":{"name":"Welcome To Colab","toc_visible":true,"provenance":[{"file_id":"/v2/external/notebooks/intro.ipynb","timestamp":1780643018499}]},"kernelspec":{"display_name":"Python 3","name":"python3"}},"nbformat":4,"nbformat_minor":0}